INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488401, 'For the only way in which a durable peace can be created is by world-wide restoration of economic activity and international trade.', 68787, 0), (488402, 'We do not want riches, we want peace and love.', 68707, 0), (488403, 'The game is my wife. It demands loyalty and responsibility, and it gives me back fulfillment and peace.', 1813, 0), (488404, 'You may call for peace as loudly as you wish, but where there is no brotherhood there can in the end be no peace.', 17597, 0), (488405, 'We''ve climbed the mighty mountain. I see the valley below, and it''s a valley of peace.', 2358, 0), (488406, 'I''m all about peace. I''m all about unity. I''m all about love.', 68176, 0), (488407, 'A peace deal requires agreements, and you don''t make agreements with your friends, you make agreements with your enemies.', 3083, 0), (488408, 'You should feel beautiful and you should feel safe. What you surround yourself with should bring you peace of mind and peace of spirit.', 36959, 0), (488409, 'Peace demands the united efforts of us all. Who can foresee what spark might ignite the fuse?', 15968, 0), (488410, 'Obedience brings peace in decision making. If we have firmly made up our minds to follow the commandments, we will not have to redecide which path to take when temptation comes our way.', 9153, 0), (488411, 'Together, we can create a world in which peace is real; in which every human being can thrive; in which all share the promise of our century. I believe we can succeed.', 30519, 0), (488412, 'Water is always a support or a healing thing apart from, you know, love or peace of mind.', 72318, 0), (488413, 'Our political machine, composed of thirteen independent sovereignties, have been perpetually operating against each other and against the federal head ever since the peace.', 68658, 0), (488414, 'I''m not claiming divinity. I''ve never claimed purity of soul. I''ve never claimed to have the answers to life. I only put out songs and answer questions as honestly as I can... But I still believe in peace, love and understanding.', 46, 0), (488415, 'Jesus said, ''Greater things of these you shall do...'' Become a peace builder, a bridge builder, not a destroyer, and the way you do that is through friendships and relationships, and through authentic character.', 4001, 0), (488416, 'Whether addressing immediate crises or building long-term foundations of peace, the United Nations will remain committed to solutions that advance the global good.', 21719, 0), (488417, 'For me, it is essential to have the inner peace and serenity of prayer in order to listen to the silence of God, which speaks to us, in our personal life and the history of our times, of the power of love.', 67385, 0), (488418, 'My court was divided between peace and war according to their various interests, but I considered only their reasons.', 65275, 0), (488419, 'Peace is its own reward.', 32, 0), (488420, 'We want peace and development in all 10 states of South Sudan - we don''t want military backing.', 75628, 0), (488421, 'Disappointment is a sticky one, because no one can steal contentment, joy, gratitude, or peace - we have to give it away.', 12208, 0), (488422, 'They may call me a sinner, but I am at peace with myself.', 15813, 0), (488423, 'Having a mind that is open to everything and attached to nothing seems to me to be one of the most basic principles that you can adopt to contribute to individual and world peace.', 21729, 0), (488424, 'A desire arises in the mind. It is satisfied immediately another comes. In the interval which separates two desires a perfect calm reigns in the mind. It is at this moment freed from all thought, love or hate. Complete peace equally reigns between two mental waves.', 62960, 0), (488425, 'Let me just say: Peace to you, if you''re willing to fight for it.', 50645, 0), (488426, 'If there must be trouble, let it be in my day, that my child may have peace.', 1131, 0), (488427, 'True humility is contentment.', 4754, 0), (488428, 'Even peace may be purchased at too high a price.', 1077, 0), (488429, 'An army of principles can penetrate where an army of soldiers cannot.', 1131, 0), (488430, 'First keep peace with yourself, then you can also bring peace to others.', 946, 0), (488431, 'Success is measured by your discipline and inner peace.', 47904, 0), (488432, 'In peace, the Middle East, the ancient cradle of civilization, will become invigorated and transformed. Throughout its lands there will be freedom of movement of people, of ideas, of goods.', 68756, 0), (488433, 'To plunder, to slaughter, to steal, these things they misname empire; and where they make a wilderness, they call it peace.', 3582, 0), (488434, 'Today, we have two Vietnams, side by side, North and South, exchanging and working. We may not agree with all that North Vietnam is doing, but they are living in peace. I would look for a better human rights record for North Vietnam, but they are living side by side.', 75629, 0), (488435, 'Give a child love, laughter and peace, not AIDS.', 1722, 0), (488436, 'I had daydreams and fantasies when I was growing up. I always wanted to live in a log cabin at the foot of a mountain. I would ride my horse to town and pick up provisions. Then return to the cabin, with a big open fire, a record player and peace.', 52060, 0), (488437, 'Nothing has brought me more love, joy and peace than being a good husband and good daddy.', 68352, 0), (488438, 'Peace is a day-to-day problem, the product of a multitude of events and judgments. Peace is not an ''is,'' it is a ''becoming.''', 15968, 0), (488439, 'The purpose of all wars, is peace.', 63060, 0), (488440, 'Every goal, every action, every thought, every feeling one experiences, whether it be consciously or unconsciously known, is an attempt to increase one''s level of peace of mind.', 74808, 0), (488441, 'To attain inner peace you must actually give your life, not just your possessions. When you at last give your life - bringing into alignment your beliefs and the way you live then, and only then, can you begin to find inner peace.', 47088, 0), (488442, 'Care less for your harvest than for how it is shared and your life will have meaning and your heart will have peace.', 5155, 0), (488443, 'We should use our old moral values and our love of peace as the foundation of national reconstruction and look forward to the day when we shall become leaders in world reconstruction upon lines of international justice and good will.', 67071, 0), (488444, 'Before we went on any protest, whether it was sit-ins or the freedom rides or any march, we prepared ourselves, and we were disciplined. We were committed to the way of peace - the way of non-violence - the way of love - the way of life as the way of living.', 36727, 0), (488445, 'My belief is in the chaos of the world and that you have to find your peace within the chaos and that you still have to find some sort of mission.', 1309, 0), (488446, 'As an artist I come to sing, but as a citizen, I will always speak for peace, and no one can silence me in this.', 3412, 0), (488447, 'Every human longs for peace and love.', 75630, 0), (488448, 'Our souls may lose their peace and even disturb other people''s, if we are always criticizing trivial actions - which often are not real defects at all, but we construe them wrongly through our ignorance of their motives.', 69044, 0), (488449, 'The Union, which can alone insure internal peace, and external security to each State, Must and Shall be Preserved, cost what it may in time, treasure, and blood.', 67727, 0), (488450, 'The United States has the burden to lead for peace. And not just peace - we need peace with justice, a much harder goal.', 71477, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488451, 'Peace is a natural effect of trade.', 48659, 0), (488452, 'There is no greater feeling than hanging out with my dogs, or just walking around the land with our horses. My rescue ranch is is where I feel the most at peace and where I''m reminded of the simple things in life and let the chaos of my crazy work life fade away.', 9111, 0), (488453, 'After four years at the United Nations I sometimes yearn for the peace and tranquility of a political convention.', 69260, 0), (488454, 'There can never be peace between nations until there is first known that true peace which is within the souls of men.', 2576, 0), (488455, 'But, my dear sirs, when peace does come, you may call on me for any thing. Then will I share with you the last cracker, and watch with you to shield your homes and families against danger from every quarter.', 65193, 0), (488456, 'Peace secured by slavish submission is not peace.', 68664, 0), (488457, 'A conqueror is always a lover of peace.', 2677, 0), (488458, 'Peace without justice is tyranny.', 53013, 0), (488459, 'Take away the violence and who will hear the men of peace?', 4386, 0), (488460, 'You may gain temporary appeasement by a policy of concession to violence, but you do not gain lasting peace that way.', 16089, 0), (488461, 'We all lose somebody we care about and want to find some comforting way of dealing with it, something that will give us a little closure, a little peace.', 131, 0), (488462, 'Nothing is wrong with peace and love. It is all the more regrettable that so many of Christ''s followers seem to disagree.', 1716, 0), (488463, 'I believe that peace with the Palestinians is most urgent - urgent than ever before. It is necessary. It is crucial. It is possible. A delay may worsen its chances. Israel and the Palestinians are, in my judgment, ripe today to restart the peace process.', 4770, 0), (488464, 'Peace is something very dear. If you''ve been through wars and operations and battles, you want peace.', 45690, 0), (488465, 'I do believe in God. But you won''t find me visiting temples every now and then. I believe in self-realization. Peace of mind matters a lot to me. What''s the point in doing something just for the sake of it? I''d rather do something I like doing as long as I''m being true to myself.', 66892, 0), (488466, 'Everything I want to do, and to accomplish, is on the other side of the universe. That''s peace of mind, energy, freedom. And I''m making myself ready to go, joyfully and willingly. I think I''m ready to be everybody''s friend, and to do anything for anybody. It''s heavy.', 69545, 0), (488467, 'The question that we must ask is whether we are making progress toward the goal of universal peace. Or are we caught up on a treadmill of history, turning forever on the axle of mindless aggression and self-destruction?', 73906, 0), (488468, 'In our quest for peace, we should constantly ask ourselves what we should do to create conditions in which peace can prosper.', 73906, 0), (488469, 'Some might complain that nuclear disarmament is little more than a dream. But that ignores the very tangible benefits disarmament would bring for all humankind. Its success would strengthen international peace and security. It would free up vast and much-needed resources for social and economic development. It would advance the rule of law.', 21719, 0), (488470, 'Don''t stand back with your arms folded', 67385, 0), (488471, 'I have seen (as far as it can be seen) many persons changed in a moment from the spirit of horror, fear, and despair to the spirit of hope, joy, peace; and from sinful desires, till then reigning over them, to a pure desire of doing the will of God.', 1728, 0), (488472, 'Enigma is really an investment in peace of mind. I keep a lot of confidential information on my laptop. I''m usually very careful about keeping my laptop under close physical control but had an unfortunate lapse and left it on a plane. That could have cost me dearly if not for the Enigma.', 70001, 0), (488473, 'I do not support peace in the Middle East. And I do not support Arafat. He is a stupid, incompetent fool!', 71356, 0), (488474, 'Whoever wishes peace among peoples must fight statism.', 9998, 0), (488475, 'The United States is not a nation to which peace is a necessity.', 18162, 0), (488476, 'The world''s people all share the earnest aspiration to have peace, stability, justice and cooperation.', 71561, 0), (488477, 'If anything I consider myself non-violent, I''m from the hippy era, peace, love, groovy.', 75631, 0), (488478, 'Wars are, of course, as a rule to be avoided; but they are far better than certain kinds of peace.', 1674, 0), (488479, 'I like doves. They look so beautiful, like a woman. For me they represent peace and love and purity. And sometimes they''re seen as the messengers of God, so they''re important to me because I''m a Christian.', 74567, 0), (488480, 'Hobbits are an unobtrusive but very ancient people, more numerous formerly than they are today; for they love peace and quiet and good tilled earth: a well-ordered and well-farmed countryside was their favourite haunt.', 65, 0), (488481, 'My day job may be exhausting, but cooking is my peace. My dream is to have a big family with lots of grandkids. And we''ll get together every Sunday for a hearty dinner at our house, and we''ll all live in flavorful bliss, happily ever after.', 67832, 0), (488482, 'In the Middle East, it is clear that peace will never be reached without solving the Israeli-Palestinian conflict. A two-state solution must be found and enforced.', 67551, 0), (488483, 'Climate change, in some regions, has aggravated conflict over scarce land, and could well trigger large-scale migration in the decades ahead. And rising sea levels put at risk the very survival of all small island states. These and other implications for peace and security have implications for the United Nations itself.', 21719, 0), (488484, 'Peace should be understood in a human way - in a broad social, political and economic way. Peace is threatened by unjust economic, social and political order, absence of democracy, environmental degradation and absence of human rights.', 3626, 0), (488485, 'I most sincerely wish that the world in which we live be free from the threat of a nuclear holocaust and from the ruinous arms race. It is my cherished desire that peace be not separated from freedom which is the right of every nation. This I desire and for this I pray.', 63581, 0), (488486, 'Peace is rarely denied to the peaceful.', 1988, 0), (488487, 'Change is certain. Peace is followed by disturbances; departure of evil men by their return. Such recurrences should not constitute occasions for sadness but realities for awareness, so that one may be happy in the interim.', 165, 0), (488488, 'Instead of a man of peace and love, I have become a man of violence and revenge.', 75630, 0), (488489, 'On all the peaks lies peace.', 282, 0), (488490, 'The minute you got the Nobel Peace Prize, things that I said yesterday, with nobody paying too much attention, I say the same things after I got it - oh! It was quite crucial for people, and it helped our morale because apartheid did look invincible.', 2109, 0), (488491, 'Today, hundreds of millions dwell in freedom, from the Baltic to the Adriatic, from the Western Approaches to the Aegean. And while we must never take this for granted, the first purpose of the European Union - to secure peace - has been achieved and we should pay tribute to all those in the EU, alongside Nato, who made that happen.', 28607, 0), (488492, 'I am a strong believer that without justice, there is no peace. No lasting peace, anyway.', 1380, 0), (488493, 'He that would live in peace and at ease must not speak all he knows or all he sees.', 1077, 0), (488494, 'If you want peace, you don''t talk to your friends. You talk to your enemies.', 2109, 0), (488495, 'As I came to power peacefully, so shall I keep it.', 67376, 0), (488496, 'The simplification of life is one of the steps to inner peace. A persistent simplification will create an inner and outer well-being that places harmony in one''s life.', 47088, 0), (488497, 'Complete peace equally reigns between two mental waves.', 62960, 0), (488498, 'I think it''s naive to pray for world peace if we''re not going to change the form in which we live.', 26193, 0), (488499, 'Islam means peace.', 1851, 0), (488500, 'We believe in peace and peaceful development, not only for ourselves but for people all over the world.', 67654, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488501, 'Until he extends his circle of compassion to include all living things, man will not himself find peace.', 1006, 0), (488502, 'We have a long way to go before we are able to hear the voices of everyone on earth, but I believe that providing voices and building bridges is essential for the World Peace we all wish for.', 69476, 0), (488503, 'Five enemies of peace inhabit with us - avarice, ambition, envy, anger, and pride; if these were to be banished, we should infallibly enjoy perpetual peace.', 66050, 0), (488504, 'Life is wonderful beautiful journey. Every episode of my life is like a dream, and I am at peace and happy with what life has given me.', 75632, 0), (488505, 'Smoke the pipe of peace, bury the tomahawk, and become one nation.', 73638, 0), (488506, 'Nuclear disarmament and non-proliferation are not utopian ideals. They are critical to global peace and security.', 21719, 0), (488507, 'I believe it is peace in our time.', 68662, 0), (488508, 'There can be no vulnerability without risk; there can be no community without vulnerability; there can be no peace, and ultimately no life, without community.', 624, 0), (488509, 'World-wide practice of Conservation and the fair and continued access by all nations to the resources they need are the two indispensable foundations of continuous plenty and of permanent peace.', 68848, 0), (488510, 'My passion stems from seeking world peace and finding how we can live together creatively rather than violently.', 73530, 0), (488511, 'Be good, keep your feet dry, your eyes open, your heart at peace and your soul in the joy of Christ.', 123, 0), (488512, 'If you want to make peace, you don''t talk to your friends. You talk to your enemies.', 34585, 0), (488513, 'If man does find the solution for world peace it will be the most revolutionary reversal of his record we have ever known.', 68681, 0), (488514, 'Peace, unity and harmony!', 73545, 0), (488515, 'For me, peace is a fundamental human right of every child; it is inevitable and divine.', 68125, 0), (488516, 'The only people that can make peace are the parties to the conflict, and just as they are responsible for the conflict and its consequences, so should they be given responsibility and recognition for the peace.', 70984, 0), (488517, 'Many African leaders refuse to send their troops on peace keeping missions abroad because they probably need their armies to intimidate their own populations.', 29992, 0), (488518, 'If I were asked to name the chief benefit of the house, I should say: the house shelters day-dreaming, the house protects the dreamer, the house allows one to dream in peace.', 3079, 0), (488519, 'Nothing is more conducive to peace of mind than not having any opinion at all.', 68283, 0), (488520, 'We all want peace. Unfortunately, there are times when peace must be defended by fighting terror and tyranny.', 67636, 0), (488521, 'There is a criterion by which you can judge whether the thoughts you are thinking and the things you are doing are right for you. The criterion is: Have they brought you inner peace?', 47088, 0), (488522, 'The peace and justice movement has to expand and not run away from the plight of gang members.', 75633, 0), (488523, 'We would fight not for the political future of a distant city, rather for principles whose destruction would ruin the possibility of peace and security for the peoples of the earth.', 68662, 0), (488524, 'The years of the economic depression have been years of political reaction, and that is why the economic crisis has generated a world peace crisis.', 68699, 0), (488525, 'To solve the problem of organizing world peace we must establish world law and order.', 68699, 0), (488526, 'There are two traditions in Northern Ireland. There are two main religious denominations. But there is only one true moral denomination. And it wants peace.', 75077, 0), (488527, 'Let peace, descending from her native heaven, bid her olives spring amidst the joyful nations; and plenty, in league with commerce, scatter blessings from her copious hand!', 14584, 0), (488528, 'I am grateful for the opportunities I have been given to participate in that work as a representative of my country, Canada, whose people have, I think, shown their devotion to peace.', 17580, 0), (488529, 'For Pleasure, Delight, Peace and Felicity live in method and temperance.', 26393, 0), (488530, 'There can be no peace in the world so long as a large proportion of the population lack the necessities of life and believe that a change of the political and economic system will make them available. World peace must be based on world plenty.', 68811, 0), (488531, 'All of us deserve a greater peace of mind, knowing that our children are better protected wherever they are.', 66765, 0), (488532, 'One can not reflect in streaming water. Only those who know internal peace can give it to others.', 15, 0), (488533, 'We receive His peace when we ask Him for it. We keep His peace by extending it to others. Those are the keys and there are no others.', 534, 0), (488534, 'In a few decades, the relationship between the environment, resources and conflict may seem almost as obvious as the connection we see today between human rights, democracy and peace.', 17733, 0), (488535, 'If peace cannot be maintained with honour, it is no longer peace.', 4646, 0), (488536, 'We have peace with Israel. We''re actually the last man standing. So there is going to be immense pressure and people asking, ''Why are we having this relationship when it''s not benefiting anybody?'' Obviously, my answer is you always benefit from peace.', 30519, 0), (488537, 'When we take our eyes off the whirl of day-to-day activity and concentrate on honoring Him and following in His way, we find a consistent peace that carries us through both plenty and poverty.', 67762, 0), (488538, 'I''m just an old hippie. You know, peace and love.', 75634, 0), (488539, 'Bob Marley performed the ''One Love Peace'' concert in Jamaica with the two different warring political sides. There''s always been that in black music and culture in general. It''s no surprise because black music is such a reflection of what''s going on in black life. It''s not unusual for hip-hop.', 5050, 0), (488540, 'There is a thin line between peace of the brave and peace of the hostage... between compromise - even calculated risk - and irresponsibility and capitulation.', 60701, 0), (488541, 'As most of the population suffers through life, barely surviving, disappointed and confused day after day, hopeless, wondering what happened to their strong and beautiful country, it is in the media''s power to restore, if not some of our quality of life, at least a bit of our peace of mind.', 69338, 0), (488542, 'A heartsong doesn''t have to be a song in your heart. It doesn''t have to be talking about love and peace. It can just be your message. It can be your feeling. Some people might even call it a conscience, even though that''s not really what it is. It''s your message, what you feel like you need to do.', 22029, 0), (488543, 'Although Omaha is my birthplace and the place I grew up, I don''t see myself spending extended amounts of time there. I feel almost more comfortable and more at peace in New York.', 69022, 0), (488544, 'I''ve got to be able to get my time off whether it''s just enjoying my house or the peace and quiet of my family and being there and cooking for them. I love doing that. I also love doing leisure things. I ride horses. I love to shop. I love to drive!', 75149, 0), (488545, 'We are all familiar with the dove carrying an olive branch as a peace offering. The jewelry I''ve created pays tribute both to the messenger''s noble mission and gardens as a refuge of peace and tranquility.', 68030, 0), (488546, 'Poverty is the absence of all human rights. The frustrations, hostility and anger generated by abject poverty cannot sustain peace in any society.', 3626, 0), (488547, 'When life doesn''t make sense, we can still have peace.', 710, 0), (488548, 'I like my peace and quiet whenever I can grab it.', 6613, 0), (488549, 'It is heroic to prepare for war with a tyrant power. Patriots will always win the admiration of mankind for daring to meet the bloodshed of battle for their country''s liberty. But the patriot who is willing to go to that sacrifice will be the first to condemn the aimless and secret shedding of blood in time of peace.', 1787, 0), (488550, 'If the inner world is inundated with peace, then the nightmare of world war cannot even come into being.', 4786, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488551, 'I love Miami; I miss it so much. I miss the beach, the peace it brings you. I love the sound and smell of the sea.', 69781, 0), (488552, 'The vast majority of Malaysians are sensible people; they''re moderates, they want peace, they want harmonious race relations at home. They look for national unity.', 72764, 0), (488553, 'Tolerance, like any aspect of peace, is forever a work in progress, never completed, and, if we''re as intelligent as we like to think we are, never abandoned.', 3278, 0), (488554, 'When I go home and get off tour, I''d like to have a peace of mind. I like to chill. I don''t like everything to be all chaotic like how it is when I step outside, you know?', 69060, 0), (488555, 'Jesus said, ''Blessed are the peacemakers.'' And I think a lot of people don''t understand that there''s a difference between a peace lover and a peacemaker. Everybody loves peace, but wearing jewelry around your neck and saying ''I love peace'' doesn''t bring it.', 17681, 0), (488556, 'My new hotels will play a leading role in promoting world peace.', 11167, 0), (488557, 'Releasing the invisible ties to those who have left you, betrayed you, disappointed you or hurt you, you open up to higher realms of love, peace and joy.', 5671, 0), (488558, 'You may not be able to change the course of government, but you can achieve some peace. And books were the path to that. I grew up in a house where books were everywhere.', 1309, 0), (488559, 'I am in favor of a foreign policy that will cultivate relations of peace with all nations, and I will never give my influence, either as a private citizen or a public servant, for war, so long as it can be honorably avoided.', 75635, 0), (488560, 'The olive branch has been consecrated to peace, palm branches to victory, the laurel to conquest and poetry, the myrtle to love and pleasure, the cypress to mourning, and the willow to despondency.', 3921, 0), (488561, 'The cry of the oppressed has entered not only into my ears, but into my soul, so that while I live, I cannot hold my peace.', 75636, 0), (488562, 'A consecrated Christian life is ever shedding light and comfort and peace.', 4150, 0), (488563, 'There is very little room for relaxation, but as long as I capitalize on those brief moments of peace, I''m okay with that.', 71512, 0), (488564, 'There is a marvelous peace in not publishing. It''s peaceful. Still. Publishing is a terrible invasion of my privacy.', 268, 0), (488565, 'We''re in the last days, man - I truly, in my heart, believe that. It''s written. I could go on with biblical situations and things my grandma told me. But it''s about being at peace with myself and making good with the people around me.', 22894, 0), (488566, 'Everybody knows that love is better than hate, and peace is better than war.', 62855, 0), (488567, 'Our leaders must hear us speaking on behalf of our brothers and sisters in South Sudan. If the moral duty to save lives and work toward peace is not compelling enough to drive decision-makers, we must remind them that we care and will hold them accountable.', 37699, 0), (488568, 'To craftsmanship we shall add statesmanship in the capitol of peace.', 75637, 0), (488569, 'When the war was in progress, England and France agreed wholeheartedly with the Fourteen Points. As soon as the war was won, England, France, and Italy tried to frustrate Wilson''s program because it was in conflict with their imperialist policies. As a consequence, the Peace Treaty was one of the most unequal treaties ever negotiated in history.', 67071, 0), (488570, 'Some men know that a light touch of the tongue, running from a woman''s toes to her ears, lingering in the softest way possible in various places in between, given often enough and sincerely enough, would add immeasurably to world peace.', 534, 0), (488571, 'Peace and not war is the father of all things.', 9998, 0), (488572, 'Money can come and go, and fame comes and goes. Peace of mind and a relationship with God is far more important, so this is the precedent that we''ve set in our lives. The bottom line is, we all die, so Jesus is the answer.', 36674, 0), (488573, 'If they want peace, nations should avoid the pin-pricks that precede cannon shots.', 1702, 0), (488574, 'All my life, I have maintained that the people of the world can learn to live together in peace if they are not brought up in prejudice.', 52279, 0), (488575, 'The idea that the EU is somehow the guarantor of peace on the continent - that is in itself rash, in my view, and risks undermining the vital role of Nato.', 13639, 0), (488576, 'Peace will be when you accept it in your heart.', 75630, 0), (488577, 'Peace is our gift to each other.', 10, 0), (488578, 'The very first lesson that I learnt from the Qur''an was the message of unity and peace.', 61043, 0), (488579, 'The Palestinians want a state, but they have to give peace in return. What they''re trying to do in the United Nations is to get a state without giving Israel peace or giving Israel peace and security. And I think that''s, that''s wrong. That should not succeed. That should, that should fail.', 45690, 0), (488580, 'When your soul is resting, your emotions are okay, your mind is okay, and your will is at peace with God, not resisting what He''s doing.', 1206, 0), (488581, 'We on our part will stick to our independent foreign policy of peace, acting forever as a strong defender of world peace and a persistent proponent of common development.', 75638, 0), (488582, 'You can find peace amidst the storms that threaten you.', 4294, 0), (488583, 'At the end of the day, Wonder Woman is a peace seeker. But when fight arrives, she can fight. She''s a warrior, and she enjoys the adrenaline of the fight.', 67133, 0), (488584, 'My heritage has been my grounding, and it has brought me peace.', 66873, 0), (488585, 'The quiet rhythmic monotone of the wall of logs fills one with the rustic peace of a secluded nook in the woods.', 72435, 0), (488586, 'It isn''t enough to talk about peace. One must believe in it. And it isn''t enough to believe in it. One must work at it.', 141, 0), (488587, 'Let us not deceive ourselves we must elect world peace or world destruction. ', 59644, 0), (488588, 'Let love flow so that it cleanses the world. Then man can live in peace, instead of the state of turmoil he has created through his past ways of life, with all those material interests and earthly ambitions.', 29441, 0), (488589, 'The Nobel Peace Prize opened up a door in my heart.', 5358, 0), (488590, 'The European Union is the world''s most successful invention for advancing peace.', 72164, 0), (488591, 'We will not learn how to live together in peace by killing each other''s children.', 1229, 0), (488592, 'Our object should be peace within, and peace without. We want to live peacefully and maintain cordial friendly relations with our immediate neighbours and with the world at large.', 1480, 0), (488593, 'The people of the world genuinely want peace. Some day the leaders of the world are going to have to give in and give it to them.', 2119, 0), (488594, 'I want to see peace in the country.', 67338, 0), (488595, 'Guilt for being rich, and guilt thinking that perhaps love and peace isn''t enough and you have to go and get shot or something.', 46, 0), (488596, 'You do indeed have a past, but not now! And, yes, you have a future, but not now! You can consume your now with thoughts of ''then'' and ''maybe,'' but that will keep you from the inner peace you could experience.', 21729, 0), (488597, 'What we need is Star Peace and not Star Wars.', 41880, 0), (488598, 'To be misunderstood can be the writer''s punishment for having disturbed the reader''s peace. The greater the disturbance, the greater the possibility of misunderstanding.', 13920, 0), (488599, 'Peace can be promoted by the limitation of arms and by the creation of the instrumentality for peaceful settlement of controversies. But it will become a reality only through self-restraint and active effort in friendliness and helpfulness.', 7777, 0), (488600, 'In Hawaii, we have something called Ho''oponopono, where people come together to resolve crises and restore peace and balance.', 67424, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488601, 'The Honorable Elijah Muhammad teaches us that God, now, is about to establish a kingdom on this earth, based upon brotherhood and peace. And the white man is against brotherhood, and the white man is against peace.', 1730, 0), (488602, 'While conscience is our friend, all is at peace; however once it is offended, farewell to a tranquil mind.', 2618, 0), (488603, 'There is no way to peace peace is the way. ', 75639, 0), (488604, 'Consistently rated the most peaceable of all countries in the world by the Global Peace Index, Iceland has reduced its military expenditure to zero, has no armed forces, and has reduced the inequality gap between rich and poor.', 75640, 0), (488605, 'Peace is much more precious than a piece of land... let there be no more wars.', 63143, 0), (488606, 'Peace is when time doesn''t matter as it passes by.', 75641, 0), (488607, 'It is better we disintegrate in peace and not in pieces.', 75642, 0), (488608, 'If we have not peace within ourselves, it is in vain to seek it from outward sources.', 154, 0), (488609, 'It''s well known I''m a Scientologist, and that has helped me to find that inner peace in my life and it''s something that has given me great stability and tools that I use.', 26127, 0), (488610, 'A decision once taken brings peace to a man''s mind and eases his soul.', 16554, 0), (488611, 'I would like to end world hunger and create world peace, stop corruption, stop drugs getting to kids.', 75643, 0), (488612, 'Intervention only works when the people concerned seem to be keen for peace.', 1722, 0), (488613, 'China pays a great deal of attention to the Korean nuclear issue. We stand for achieving denuclearization of the peninsula in a peaceful way through dialogue and consultation to maintain peace and stability of the peninsula and Northeast Asia.', 75136, 0), (488614, 'You can only end a negotiation for peace if you begin it.', 45690, 0), (488615, 'Aside from what it teaches you, there is simply the indescribable degree of peace that can be achieved on a sailing vessel at sea. I guess a combination of hard work and the seemingly infinite expanse of the sea - the profound solitude - that does it for me.', 72618, 0), (488616, 'I always wanted to see people''s lives transformed from depression and anxiety to joy and peace.', 11168, 0), (488617, 'I believe that the topic of chemical weapons is critically important for international peace and security, and I take note of the ongoing debate over what course of action should be taken by the international community. All those actions should be taken within the framework of the U.N. Charter, as a matter of principle.', 21719, 0), (488618, 'I think that American women are further along than any other women in the world. But you can''t have peace in a world in which some women or some men or some nations are at different stages of development. There is so much work to be done.', 64860, 0), (488619, 'Our armed forces will fight for peace in Iraq, a peace built on more secure foundations than are found today in the Middle East. Even more important, they will fight for two human conditions of even greater value than peace: liberty and justice.', 9128, 0), (488620, 'Bob Marley stood for universal peace and love. He tried to break racial barriers.', 33126, 0), (488621, 'I want a world of peace. I''m not interested in bombs. I''m not interested in wars. I''m interested in peace.', 50602, 0), (488622, 'Peace hath higher tests of manhood, than battle ever knew.', 997, 0), (488623, 'Peace is liberty in tranquillity.', 1306, 0), (488624, 'We want to take good tidings home to our people, that they may sleep in peace.', 68770, 0), (488625, 'I happen to dig being able to use whatever mystique I have to further the idea of peace.', 75644, 0), (488626, 'It is understanding that gives us an ability to have peace. When we understand the other fellow''s viewpoint, and he understands ours, then we can sit down and work out our differences.', 16121, 0), (488627, 'Israel is no longer a people that dwells alone, and has to join the global journey toward peace, reconciliation and international cooperation.', 21741, 0), (488628, 'In fact, because of this deep desire for peace, the ruling class leaders of this land, from 1945 on, stepped up the hysteria and propaganda to drive into American minds the false notion that danger threatened them from the East.', 3412, 0), (488629, 'We believe world peace is inevitable.', 14652, 0), (488630, 'Even the holy men who lived before the coming of Christ understood that God had in mind plans of peace for the human race.', 65719, 0), (488631, 'I want you to give all these chiefs of the soldiers here to understand that we are for peace, and that we have made peace, that we may not be mistaken by them for enemies.', 68770, 0), (488632, 'The plan shows that the twenty million people in the German democratic Republic and in the democratic sector of Berlin think only of peace, and that they are working for freedom and peaceful prosperity.', 75645, 0), (488633, 'I have traveled a long road from the battlefield to the peace table.', 34585, 0), (488634, 'We need new partnerships for peace and security.', 67728, 0), (488635, 'A sign that a peace association is going adrift is its exclusion of other political parties, with whom it could collaborate effectively on most of the problems besetting the cause of peace.', 73796, 0), (488636, 'We must join with the tens of millions all over the world who see in peace our most sacred responsibility.', 3412, 0), (488637, 'Peace goes into the making of a poem as flour goes into the making of bread.', 12, 0), (488638, 'Martin Luther King Jr. is remembered as our prince of peace, of civil rights. We owe him something major that will keep his memory alive.', 30247, 0), (488639, 'When I was in the Peace Corps I never made a phone call. I was in Central Africa; I didn''t make a phone call for two years. I was in Uganda for another four years and I didn''t make a phone call. So for six years I didn''t make a phone call, but I wrote letters, I wrote short stories, I wrote books.', 1979, 0), (488640, 'The myth of redemptive violence - Caesar, peace, and victory - is in people''s bones so deeply, we aren''t even aware of it. You crush the opposition; that''s how we bring peace.', 2056, 0), (488641, 'I think that peace is, in many ways, a precondition of joy.', 25711, 0), (488642, 'I''ve made peace with the fact that the things that I thought were weaknesses or flaws were just me. I like them.', 68422, 0), (488643, 'The word ''success'' - who''s defining it? It''s about whether or not it makes me feel good. Four billion people don''t have to see or hear it. If I''ve enjoyed the process of creation and I''m at peace, then what happens next is just entertainment. If mass appeal were actually something, Marilyn Monroe wouldn''t be dead.', 64763, 0), (488644, 'Patriarchy is a fundamental imbalance underlying society And it''s one we rarely address because it''s so universal. But as I get older, I see that peace is a product of balance.', 1251, 0), (488645, 'To discover your mission and put it into action - instead of worrying on the sidelines - is to find peace of mind and a heart full of love.', 75640, 0), (488646, 'I was profoundly moved to be the first United Nations Secretary-General to attend the Peace Memorial Ceremony in Hiroshima. I also visited Nagasaki. Sadly, we know the terrible humanitarian consequences from the use of even one weapon. As long as such weapons exist, so, too, will the risks of use and proliferation.', 21719, 0), (488647, 'I think people need to know that there''s great peace and joy in knowing the Lord - the Lord Jesus Christ - as your savior.', 72029, 0), (488648, 'While the lab plays an enormous role, research is also influenced by inner peace of mind and one''s family environment, depending on what stage of one''s life and career a scientist is at.', 70303, 0), (488649, 'I''ve often made critical comments about settlement expansion in the occupied West Bank and in east Jerusalem, and my position hasn''t changed. At the same time, it''s equally important to me that the two sides, both Israel and the Palestinians, work towards a durable peace settlement: that''s to say a viable two-state solution.', 67556, 0), (488650, 'Pope John Paul II was a man of peace, a friend of the Jewish nation... and worked for the historic reconciliation between the nations and for the renewal of diplomatic ties between Israel and the Vatican at the end of 1993.', 67007, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488651, 'Black people need some peace. White people need some peace. And we are going to have to fight. We''re going to have to struggle. We''re going to have to struggle relentlessly to bring about some peace, because the people that we''re asking for peace, they are a bunch of megalomaniac warmongers, and they don''t even understand what peace means.', 50645, 0), (488652, 'In the ''60s we fought for peace, when the Vietnam war was on. We were against the cops and against the politicians, and there was a lot of waving banners and all that. And I think in a way, just as they were enjoying that machoism of war, we were enjoying the machismo of being anti-war, you know?', 1121, 0), (488653, 'Now God be praised, I will die in peace.', 45346, 0), (488654, 'Love, peace and soul.', 71334, 0), (488655, 'In every man the memory of the struggles and the heroes of the past is alive. But these memories are not incompatible with the desire for peace in the future.', 67585, 0), (488656, 'I build a kind of wall between myself and t he model so that I can paint in peace behind it. Otherwise, she might say something that confuses and distracts me.', 7791, 0), (488657, 'Then I realized that secrecy is actually to the detriment of my own peace of mind and self, and that I could still sustain my belief in privacy and be authentic and transparent at the same time. It was a pretty revelatory moment, and there''s been a liberating force that''s come from it.', 21687, 0), (488658, 'Just as God''s love to us believers, his children, is unalterably the same, whatever may be the manifestations of that love; and as his peace with us is the same, however much our peace may be disturbed; so it is also with regard to our being in fellowship or partnership with him: it remains unalterably the same so far as God is concerned.', 19001, 0), (488659, 'The wars don''t end when you sign peace treaties or when the years go by. They will echo on until I''m gone and all the widows and orphans are gone.', 3159, 0), (488660, 'The pageant movie I''m obsessed with is ''Miss Congeniality'', hands down! I could quote everything from that movie. I love so many scenes, but I always find myself quoting the scene when Sandra Bullock goes, ''I really do just want world peace!''', 18860, 0), (488661, 'Together, we will lead our party back to the White House, and we will lead our country back to safety, prosperity, and peace.', 64643, 0), (488662, 'I think that people want peace so much that one of these days government had better get out of their way and let them have it.', 2119, 0), (488663, 'I do not want the peace which passeth understanding, I want the understanding which bringeth peace.', 701, 0), (488664, 'A quiet mind cureth all.', 6261, 0), (488665, 'A people free to choose will always choose peace.', 1727, 0), (488666, 'There is always a certain peace in being what one is, in being that completely.', 61075, 0), (488667, 'If there is to be any peace it will come through being, not having.', 497, 0), (488668, 'One is called to live nonviolently, even if the change one works for seems impossible.', 64379, 0), (488669, 'I believe in peace. I believe in mercy.', 1851, 0), (488670, 'When you can whip any man in the world, you never know peace.', 1751, 0), (488671, 'I think that a strong Israel is the only Israel that will bring the Arabs to the peace table.', 45690, 0), (488672, 'I would rather have peace in the world than be President.', 16121, 0), (488673, 'Law enforcement officers are never ''off duty.'' They are dedicated public servants who are sworn to protect public safety at any time and place that the peace is threatened. They need all the help that they can get.', 71482, 0), (488674, 'When you find peace within yourself, you become the kind of person who can live at peace with others.', 47088, 0), (488675, 'The greatest problem all around the world today, whether in America, Japan, China Russia, India or anywhere else in the world, is that people are not in peace. People want peace.', 4902, 0), (488676, 'A man will treat a woman almost exactly the way he treats his own interior feminine. In fact, he hasn''t the ability to see a woman, objectively speaking, until he has made some kind of peace with his interior woman.', 50409, 0), (488677, 'It''s wonderful to be back. Back among the mountains that remind us of our vulnerability, our ultimate lack of control over the world we live in. Mountains that demand humility, and yield so much peace in return.', 72265, 0), (488678, 'But he is unworthy the name of a minister of the gospel of peace, who is unwilling, not only to have his name cast out as evil, but also to die for the truths of the Lord Jesus.', 46036, 0), (488679, 'If there''s no inner peace, people can''t give it to you. The husband can''t give it to you. Your children can''t give it to you. You have to give it to you.', 75646, 0), (488680, 'Like all Israelis, I yearn for peace. I see the utmost importance in taking all possible steps that will lead to a solution of the conflict with the Palestinians.', 67007, 0), (488681, 'The choice, however, is as clear now for nations as it was once for the individual: peace or extinction.', 17580, 0), (488682, 'The U.S. cannot force Sunnis, Shias, and Kurds to make peace or to act for the common good. They have been in conflict for 1,400 years.', 75647, 0), (488683, 'There is no greater responsibility resting upon peoples and governments everywhere than to make sure that enduring peace will this time - at long last - be established and maintained.', 68824, 0), (488684, 'Self-Realization Fellowship seemed like training. It was the training ground for finding a sense of peace in myself. Because that''s my job. It''s no one else''s.', 25077, 0), (488685, 'I am not saying that I''m happy about what''s going on right now in our nation, but I am at peace and I am comforted because I know that He''s on the throne. That is good enough for me.', 74738, 0), (488686, 'Weird people follow you in the streets, you can''t sit alone in a restaurant or a cafe and read a book in peace, and I think everybody values those moments of being alone.', 70658, 0), (488687, 'Any peace process after so many years of horror and terror will be long and difficult.', 71215, 0), (488688, 'Piety is not a goal but a means to attain through the purest peace of mind the highest culture.', 282, 0), (488689, 'If a nation wants to live in peace with its neighbors, it doesn''t keep rattling the saber at them.', 75648, 0), (488690, 'Such problems are not solved in one day but there is a great step toward peace and security in the region.', 55563, 0), (488691, 'May the soul of the late President Milton Obote... a long-time member of this parliament, rest in peace.', 75649, 0), (488692, 'I cannot imagine any writer who would not fight for his peace and quiet.', 23289, 0), (488693, 'You don''t kill your way to peace.', 10828, 0), (488694, 'If there are finer beings than German short hairs, I don''t know what they are. In their eyes is peace.', 34057, 0), (488695, 'Olympics for me is love, peace, united.', 67756, 0), (488696, 'Peace does exist. It exists in your heart and soul.', 1855, 0), (488697, 'In my mind the city of Ariel is a thorn in Israel''s side and a serious obstacle to peace.', 44675, 0), (488698, 'Political satire became obsolete when they awarded Henry Kissinger the Nobel Peace Prize.', 13542, 0), (488699, 'A peace talk is always difficult, always complicated.', 66598, 0), (488700, 'My life mission is to spread peace to the world.', 22029, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488701, 'My mother, may her soul rest in peace, shaped my personality; thanks to her, I have acquired many values, good traits and skills.', 26541, 0), (488702, 'Peace is one of the most precious gifts God has promised His children. I know, because for many years my life was not peaceful, and I was miserable.', 1206, 0), (488703, 'I was raised with no religious training or influence. Except the influence was to be a moral and ethical person at the secular level. And to be a peace marcher, an activist for civil rights, peace and justice.', 457, 0), (488704, 'I believe God''s keeping the records, and I believe you will be rewarded even in this life. Somehow, some way, God will make it up to you. It may be He protected you from an accident you never knew. You can''t give God something without God giving you more in return, whether it''s peace or joy or satisfaction.', 3956, 0), (488705, 'World peace is no longer some pie-in-the-sky thing, because no single person or country is going to solve it on their own.', 30074, 0), (488706, 'Peace is a gift that is embodied through the Holy Spirit through the acceptance of Christ.', 69132, 0), (488707, 'The Nobel Peace Prize has always been a joke - albeit a grim one. Alfred Bernhard Nobel famously invented dynamite and felt sorry about it.', 10731, 0), (488708, 'Only a fighting nation can make itself responsible for world peace, and such a nation must organize its material resources and manpower with the highest possible degree of efficiency.', 67633, 0), (488709, 'While the male eye zooms in on a particular element to the exclusion of all else, a woman''s gaze flickers from one tedious task to the next, to the point where we can''t distinguish between the importance of mopping the kitchen floor and achieving world peace.', 67020, 0), (488710, 'I challenged God. I said, ''God, I know that I''m a sinner. I know that I won''t probably have peace until You''re in my heart. But I will not let You in my heart until You answer me, why? Why did you take my arms and legs? Why didn''t You give me what everybody else has? God, until You answer me that question, I will not serve You.''', 1832, 0), (488711, 'My first draft is always way too long my books start out with delusions of ''War and Peace'' - and must be gently disabused. My editor is brilliant at taking me to the point where I do all the necessary cutting on my own. I like to say she''s a midwife rather than a surgeon. ', 12039, 0), (488712, 'I grew up in war and saw the United Nations help my country to recover and rebuild. That experience was a big part of what led me to pursue a career in public service. As Secretary-General, I am determined to see this organization deliver tangible, meaningful results that advance peace, development and human rights.', 21719, 0), (488713, 'It''s hard for me to stay silent when I keep hearing that peace is only attainable through war. There''s nothing more scary than watching ignorance in action.', 75650, 0), (488714, 'I believe we all want the same thing - it doesn''t matter who you are or where you''re living. We all want to be healthy, happy, to live in peace and prosper. That''s what I connect to.', 66578, 0), (488715, 'Political satire became obsolete when Henry Kissinger was awarded the Nobel peace prize.', 13542, 0), (488716, 'Secure property in hand leads to peace in mind.', 3003, 0), (488717, 'The days of the Pentagon Papers debates seem long past, when a sudden transparency yielded insight into fights over war and peace and freedom and security; the transparency afforded by Twitter and Facebook yields insights that extend no further than a lawmaker''s boundless narcissism and a culture''s pitiless prurience.', 36805, 0), (488718, 'Being a new mother was a joyful and sometimes overwhelming experience - and as the first Missouri female state legislator to have a baby while in office, having heath care for myself and my son gave me some needed peace of mind.', 72475, 0), (488719, 'I prefer the night to the day and always stay up very late. Darkness is more peaceful, and I don''t like sunshine - it hurts my eyes. When I used to live in more communal circumstances, I had to wait until everyone had gone to bed before I had the peace to write, and I still find I can get on with my writing much better at night.', 31035, 0), (488720, 'We see a new Ethiopia, a new Africa, stretching her hands of influence throughout the world, teaching man the way of life and peace, The Way to God.', 1353, 0), (488721, 'We need peace and stability in the Asia-Pacific region. It is important to have political and security stability to build up our economic growth.', 72805, 0), (488722, 'Peace in the world is everybody''s business, no matter where you live or what you do.', 75651, 0), (488723, 'If you want to be a voice for peace in the world, begin by making peace a permanent condition of your own life.', 21729, 0), (488724, 'We do not covet one inch of Lebanese territory, and the basis for the peace treaty between our two countries will be the international border, which exists now, between Rosh Haniqra and Ras en Naqura.', 68756, 0), (488725, 'I think people used to read ''War and Peace,'' and now they don''t; now they sit around with their tablets and watch ''Downton Abbey'' and ''Breaking Bad'' or whatever, and they want the things that they watch to be better so that they can feel better about themselves for watching it.', 12054, 0), (488726, 'Peace is not a state - it is a choice, and you have to remake it every day. It''s possible to get a sort of stability, a habit of peace, but it''s like an egg balanced, spinning, on its point: lose your momentum, and your equilibrium is gone, too.', 2631, 0), (488727, '''War and Peace'' goes down a lot smoother than a Dan Brown novel, let me tell you.', 69158, 0), (488728, 'War may be made by one party, but it requires two to make peace.', 63147, 0), (488729, 'I have no doubts, by the way, that Ariel Sharon really wants to move the peace process forward.', 72790, 0), (488730, 'The two basic social identities were Normal and Greaser; although a few sophisticated girls wore peace signs, hippies didn''t exist, and while a seminal punk band, Iggy and the Stooges, was playing in nearby Ann Arbor, punk didn''t exist yet, either.', 9634, 0), (488731, 'The real Likud knows how to make peace, to give up territory, and on the other hand is conservative and responsible. My world view is that of the real Likud that truly came and safeguarded the Land of Israel.', 73921, 0), (488732, 'When it comes to matters of war and peace, we must not act rashly.', 67007, 0), (488733, 'To avoid the trap of Europe fragmenting on the economy, security, and identity, we have to return to the original promises of the European project: peace, prosperity and freedom. We should have a real, adult, democratic debate about the Europe we want.', 68911, 0), (488734, 'I''m someone who thinks that the world would be a better place if there was a big middle class. I mean, middle class is peace. In a perfect world, everybody would have enough to eat and we''d be living in security. It''s obvious. I''m very happy to pay my taxes and all that. I would say I''m more of a Social Democrat.', 69509, 0), (488735, 'Ali forced us to take a look at ourselves. This brash young man who thrilled us, angered us, confused and challenged us, ultimately became a silent messenger of peace who taught us that life is best when you build bridges between people, not walls.', 22849, 0), (488736, 'Peace and security both in Europe and in the Pacific still depend on a balance of power.', 17871, 0), (488737, 'I have to forget in order to find peace in my soul and be able to forgive.', 7906, 0), (488738, 'We can''t continue with a justice of vengeance. Peace will require us to accept a certain degree of impunity it''s inevitable. ', 7906, 0), (488739, 'The only way to find peace is when you are not separated, when you are not fighting, when you part of the whole.', 188, 0), (488740, 'My primary passion is film-making. That''s the aspect of my life that defines me, completes me, and completely grounds me. Everything else - from judging a reality TV show to hosting a talk show - is just a result of me being a film-maker. I am the happiest, satisfied and at peace when I am behind the camera.', 67066, 0), (488741, 'Not one of us can rest, be happy, be at home, be at peace with ourselves, until we end hatred and division.', 36727, 0), (488742, 'Peace is neutral, and not very sexy.', 66933, 0), (488743, 'I will try and make peace between North and South Korea.', 69925, 0), (488744, 'My long struggles as a soldier of the Chinese Revolution have forced me to realize the necessity of facing hard facts. There will be neither peace, nor hope, nor future for any of us unless we honestly aim at political, social and economic justice for all peoples of the world, great and small.', 67633, 0), (488745, 'This is the way of peace: Overcome evil with good, falsehood with truth, and hatred with love.', 47088, 0), (488746, 'We will stand up for our friends in the world. And one of the most important friends is the State of Israel. My administration will be steadfast in support Israel against terrorism and violence, and in seeking the peace for which all Israelis pray.', 2358, 0), (488747, 'The great armies, accumulated to provide security and preserve the peace, carried the nations to war by their own weight.', 20910, 0), (488748, 'Peace and abstinence from European interferences are our objects, and so will continue while the present order of things in America remain uninterrupted.', 1207, 0), (488749, 'It seems like a lot of people seek their peace in things. And most of us are not even satisfied with the things we have... we always want more.', 1206, 0), (488750, 'Peace is not only better than war, but infinitely more arduous.', 266, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488751, 'Dear God, Please send to me the spirit of Your peace. Then send, dear Lord, the spirit of peace from me to all the world. Amen.', 534, 0), (488752, 'War will never cease until babies begin to come into the world with larger cerebrums and smaller adrenal glands.', 411, 0), (488753, 'Remind yourself that the greatest technique for bringing peace into your life is to always choose being kind when you have a choice between being right or being kind.', 21729, 0), (488754, 'Peace in the Middle East has been on the Obama administration''s mind from the beginning. Two days after his inauguration, the president traveled to the State Department to announce the appointment of George Mitchell as his Middle East peace negotiator.', 67439, 0), (488755, 'The man who can centre his thoughts and hopes upon something transcending self can find a certain peace in the ordinary troubles of life, which is impossible to the pure egoist.', 95, 0), (488756, 'For me, peace should provide security to the Jewish people.', 67007, 0), (488757, 'We extend our hand towards peace. Our people are committed to peace. We know that peace entails painful compromise for both sides.', 67007, 0), (488758, 'American troops around the globe are the greatest preservers of liberty and peace in the world.', 4608, 0), (488759, 'The Peace Corps is a sort of Howard Johnson''s on the main drag into maturity.', 1979, 0), (488760, 'I have to admit that I only read ''War and Peace'' when I was 40. But I knew the basics before then.', 736, 0), (488761, 'In one way or another, President Obama''s critics will dog him all the way to Oslo for the Nobel Peace Prize ceremony, and even his admirers will continue to have doubts about his accomplishments if not his promise.', 11429, 0), (488762, 'Ed Koch will never ''rest in peace.'' That was not his way. He was always nervously squirming, while making others squirm as well. Comfort was not his goal. He understood that to be a proud and assertive Jew meant never being able to leave a sigh of relief and say, ''It''s over, we are at peace, we can now put down our guard and relax.''', 17810, 0), (488763, 'I do know that some Buddhists are able to attain peace of mind.', 21702, 0), (488764, 'As a human being, I''m concerned about the world that I live in. So, I''m concerned about peace. I''m concerned about - about man''s inhumanity to man. I''m concerned about the environment.', 30074, 0), (488765, 'I''m at peace with myself. The main thing is not letting people dictate what I do or what I am.', 67024, 0), (488766, 'Power to the peaceful!', 21674, 0), (488767, 'The only solid and lasting peace between a man and his wife is, doubtless, a separation.', 68382, 0), (488768, 'The real discovery is the one which enables me to stop doing philosophy when I want to. The one that gives philosophy peace, so that it is no longer tormented by questions which bring itself into question.', 1163, 0), (488769, 'If you use weapons of war to bring about peace, you''re going to have more war and destruction.', 16899, 0), (488770, 'I always thought of myself as a moderate liberal, a fighter for peace and justice. I never thought of myself as being all that far out.', 68665, 0), (488771, 'If you talk to most ambitious people, people who are high achievers, they''re rarely at peace with what they''re doing because they need an engine to keep moving.', 68953, 0), (488772, 'The supreme need of the world is peace and good will among men. It must be peace founded upon justice and fairness, the righting of past wrong, and the securing of the future as far as possible against the evils of the past.', 63087, 0), (488773, 'More and more, I think about the role of the arts, and as an artist, I think that it''s important that I share the love and peace.', 19930, 0), (488774, 'I feel just fine about ignoring or bypassing the rights of people I have known and loved to be rendered faithfully, or to be left in peace, and out of novels.', 27793, 0), (488775, '''Pears like my heart go flutter, flutter, and then they may say, ''Peace, Peace,'' as much as they likes - I know it''s goin'' to be war!', 1799, 0), (488776, 'My family is the engine of everything, and on a personal level, I feel peace, stability, and they give me force, which is reflected on my work, my recordings, and every time that I go out on tour. They are my base, my everything.', 68293, 0), (488777, 'Without free, self-respecting, and autonomous citizens there can be no free and independent nations. Without internal peace, that is, peace among citizens and between the citizens and the state, there can be no guarantee of external peace.', 1412, 0), (488778, 'Ignorance is a menace to peace.', 67906, 0), (488779, 'I was caught up in the hysteria during the Vietnam era, which was brought about through Marxist propaganda underlying the so-called peace movement.', 72946, 0), (488780, 'We are a Nation of peace and compassion, yet these people have and will devote every fiber of their beings to the destruction of Americans and our Country.', 70086, 0), (488781, 'My father was the superintendent of the churches in the state of Montana. He was content in his beliefs. He befit the term ''true Christian.'' He would turn the other cheek. He was truly a man of peace.', 21324, 0), (488782, 'If you sing a song of peace with enough gestures and grimaces, it becomes a war song.', 42142, 0), (488783, 'It has become impossible to give up the enterprise of disarmament without abandoning the whole great adventure of building up a collective peace system.', 68699, 0), (488784, 'The forces that are driving mankind toward unity and peace are deep-seated and powerful. They are material and natural, as well as moral and intellectual.', 68699, 0), (488785, 'Let us face it, the U.N. has failed. It has failed in its mission to promote world peace.', 74679, 0), (488786, 'I feel beautiful when I''m at peace with myself. When I''m serene, when I''m a good person, when I''ve been considerate of others.', 69779, 0), (488787, 'I never will have peace of mind. I''m not constructed that way. Some things in life can be horrible.', 71967, 0), (488788, 'But while we all pray for peace, we do not always, as free citizens, support the policies that make for peace or reject those which do not. We want our own kind of peace, brought about in our own way.', 17580, 0), (488789, 'I cannot think of anything more difficult than to say something which would be worthy of this impressive and, for me, memorable occasion, and of the ideals and purposes which inspired the Nobel Peace Award.', 17580, 0), (488790, 'I just want to live in peace and quiet.', 70747, 0), (488791, 'This enemy of peace in the world today is unlike any we have seen in the past, and our military is learning from, and building on, previous successes while carrying peace and freedom into the future.', 70453, 0), (488792, 'The business of peace requires more than showing up with paint brushes, foodstuffs and an oil pipeline or two.', 72452, 0), (488793, 'As far as having peace within myself, the one way I can do that is forgiving the people who have done wrong to me. It causes more stress to build up anger. Peace is more productive.', 73104, 0), (488794, 'The Church of Christ is constituted in two orders, the clergy and the people, the one having the care of the Church that all may be ruled for the salvation of souls; the other contains kings, princes, and nobles who have to carry on secular government that all things may lead to the peace and unity of the Church.', 71289, 0), (488795, 'The attainment of the economic aims of man presupposes peace.', 9998, 0), (488796, 'Modern society, based as it is on the division of labor, can be preserved only under conditions of lasting peace.', 9998, 0), (488797, 'I go gladly to my wife and boy, and I leave this world at peace with every one in it and at peace with God.', 66828, 0), (488798, 'My different personalities leave me in peace now.', 27498, 0), (488799, 'The longing for peace is rooted in the hearts of all men. But the striving, which at present has become so insistent, cannot lay claim to such an ambition as leading the way to eternal peace, or solving all disputes among nations.', 69546, 0), (488800, 'Some people put up a peace sign with one hand. Some people put up the middle finger instead. I use two hands and put up both.', 13028, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488801, 'What could become a danger to world peace is Iran''s nuclear program and the country''s open threat to annihilate Israel.', 73571, 0), (488802, 'Imagine the peace symbol. The peace symbol has three pieces in it. One piece is emotion, that''s your body. Another piece has spirit in it, that''s your fuel. Another piece has intellect in it and that''s your steering wheel. You can never overdo the fuel that goes into the body, which is the emotions and the steering wheel to drive it.', 68179, 0), (488803, 'We must all make peace so that we can all live in peace.', 9266, 0), (488804, 'Let us all pledge to protect this opportunity in order to see that the wish of peace becomes a true and daily fact in this region.', 72491, 0), (488805, 'Being a movie star, and this applies to all of them, means being looked at from every possible direction. You are never left at peace, you''re just fair game.', 1599, 0), (488806, 'Now for my own case, I bless the Lord that, for all that hath been said of me, my conscience doth not condemn me. I do not say I am free of sin, but I am at peace with God through a slain Mediator; and I believe that there is no salvation but only in Christ.', 68026, 0), (488807, 'I like peace and solitude and silence.', 18126, 0), (488808, 'I can see in your eyes, I can see in your faces, I can see you cry. But what I want to say, there''s no reason to cry. Do not, in the name of peace, go in the streets and riot.', 70342, 0), (488809, 'I will go on my knees and ask the Liberian people to participate in bringing peace and stability to our country.', 70342, 0), (488810, 'Economic integration is the path to riches and peace.', 75652, 0), (488811, 'I am looking forward and I am hoping that I will be the catalyst that makes India and Pakistan live for peace forever.', 75653, 0), (488812, 'When I received the news of the Nobel Peace Award, I could not believe it. I told my father, ''I think they have the wrong name, Dad. Please, can you talk to this man on the phone? I''m busy cooking!''', 75651, 0), (488813, 'Peace is not wimpy. It''s about sitting down and negotiating with people you hate. Ultimately, all occupation ends, and you have to deal with the enemy.', 75651, 0), (488814, 'Someday when peace has returned to this odd world I want to come to London again and stand on a certain balcony on a moonlit night and look down upon the peaceful silver curve of the Thames with its dark bridges.', 9247, 0), (488815, 'For hundreds of millions of Americans who believe in God, prayer is our bridge between Earth and Heaven, our way of opening our hearts to the Lord. Through this intimate relationship we find peace and guidance.', 71480, 0), (488816, 'When I create an image that helps someone - even just myself - find peace, then I''ve attained my goal.', 71889, 0), (488817, 'After living out of a suitcase for years, it''s a feeling of peace to wake up in the night and know where I am.', 70245, 0), (488818, 'I wish the Peace Corps and its volunteers continued success and perseverance. We are grateful for their contributions to society and dedication to providing assistance where it is needed. May the Peace Corps continue its legacy of service, both at home and abroad.', 67695, 0), (488819, 'As a civil rights leader, Mrs. King''s vision of racial peace and nonviolent social change was a fortifying staple in advancing the civil rights movement.', 74159, 0), (488820, 'Man does find in Nature deliverance from himself, oblivion of his past, with peace and purity!', 71953, 0), (488821, 'Of one thing I am certain, the body is not the measure of healing, peace is the measure.', 4867, 0), (488822, 'If the union between England and America is a powerful factor in the cause of peace, a new Triple Alliance between the Teutonic race and the two branches of the Anglo-Saxon race will be a still more potent influence in the future of the world.', 75654, 0), (488823, 'Peace has to be created, in order to be maintained. It will never be achieved by passivity and quietism.', 1649, 0), (488824, 'I want peace. I want to see if somewhere there isn''t something left in life of charm and grace.', 656, 0), (488825, 'We love peace, but not peace at any price.', 6072, 0), (488826, 'We have to acknowledge peace is in danger and mankind still has not realised the priority to be given to world dialogue versus armed contradiction and bloodshed.', 68820, 0), (488827, 'We call upon all sides to stop hostilities and restart peace talks.', 68820, 0), (488828, 'I don''t know whether war is an interlude during peace, or peace an interlude during war.', 4926, 0), (488829, 'It seems to be that when these communist regimes take over - if you look at the example of Vietnam or Cambodia or Nicaragua - that even in conditions of peace they don''t seem to be able to figure out how to support their people, and the human suffering is enormous.', 75655, 0), (488830, 'Peace is not the product of a victory or a command. It has no finishing line, no final deadline, no fixed definition of achievement. Peace is a never-ending process, the work of many decisions.', 43349, 0), (488831, 'If the world would only build temples to Machinery in the abstract then everything would be perfect. The painter and sculptor would have plenty to do, and could, in complete peace and suitably honored, pursue their trade without further trouble.', 38151, 0), (488832, 'We should learn to live and love our neighbors as ourselves for the sake of peace and progress.', 70772, 0), (488833, 'A babe in the house is a well-spring of pleasure, a messenger of peace and love, a resting place for innocence on earth, a link between angels and men.', 13498, 0), (488834, 'May peace rule the universe, may peace rule in kingdoms and empires, may peace rule in states and in the lands of the potentates, may peace rule in the house of friends and may peace also rule in the house of enemies.', 2888, 0), (488835, 'The quest for peace begins in the home, in the school and in the workplace.', 68774, 0), (488836, 'The Dove, on silver pinions, winged her peaceful way.', 64960, 0), (488837, 'If I''m going to be staying up until 3 A.M., it should be for world peace and not shampoo sales.', 67622, 0), (488838, 'I declare that I will establish peace in this world.', 4902, 0), (488839, 'Be at peace with your own soul, then heaven and earth will be at peace with you.', 46450, 0), (488840, 'When I play with my band around the U.S.A., the most requested song is ''Peace Frog.''', 72866, 0), (488841, 'Every time I''m in Georgia, I eat a peach for peace.', 73542, 0), (488842, 'A State in the grip of neo-colonialism is not master of its own destiny. It is this factor which makes neo-colonialism such a serious threat to world peace.', 72643, 0), (488843, 'Peace is the first thing the angels sang.', 65323, 0), (488844, 'In the whole round of human affairs little is so fatal to peace as misunderstanding.', 62203, 0), (488845, 'This is an era of violent peace.', 75656, 0), (488846, 'Do not dwell in the past, do not dream of the future, concentrate the mind on the present moment.', 63441, 0), (488847, 'Because of your smile, you make life more beautiful.', 394, 0), (488848, 'Lighten up, just enjoy life, smile more, laugh more, and don''t get so worked up about things.', 63679, 0), (488849, 'Very little is needed to make a happy life; it is all within yourself, in your way of thinking.', 267, 0), (488850, 'The most important thing is to enjoy your life - to be happy - it''s all that matters.', 999, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488851, 'Life is a dream for the wise, a game for the fool, a comedy for the rich, a tragedy for the poor.', 71991, 0), (488852, 'Just when I think I have learned the way to live, life changes.', 9901, 0), (488853, 'Change is the law of life. And those who look only to the past or present are certain to miss the future.', 1680, 0), (488854, 'The only rule is don''t be boring and dress cute wherever you go. Life is too short to blend in.', 50391, 0), (488855, 'Life is like a roller coaster, live it, be happy, enjoy life.', 2001, 0), (488856, 'I''m lucky in having found the perfect partner to spend my life with.', 41881, 0), (488857, 'Slow down and enjoy life. It''s not only the scenery you miss by going to fast - you also miss the sense of where you are going and why.', 1373, 0), (488858, 'To be free is to have achieved your life.', 355, 0), (488859, 'Life is a journey that must be traveled no matter how bad the roads and accommodations.', 2204, 0), (488860, 'My theory on life is that life is beautiful. Life doesn''t change. You have a day, and a night, and a month, and a year. We people change - we can be miserable or we can be happy. It''s what you make of your life.', 26541, 0), (488861, 'This life is like a swimming pool. You dive into the water, but you can''t see how deep it is.', 69768, 0), (488862, 'It is not the years in your life but the life in your years that counts.', 69260, 0), (488863, 'If you are not too long, I will wait here for you all my life.', 40, 0), (488864, 'I decided to fly through the air and live in the sunlight and enjoy life as much as I could.', 67044, 0), (488865, 'Life was always a matter of waiting for the right moment to act.', 34, 0), (488866, 'Life is a series of natural and spontaneous changes. Don''t resist them - that only creates sorrow. Let reality be reality. Let things flow naturally forward in whatever way they like.', 15, 0), (488867, 'Open your eyes, look within. Are you satisfied with the life you''re living?', 7, 0), (488868, 'All you need in this life is ignorance and confidence, and then success is sure.', 286, 0), (488869, 'Life is not easy for any of us. But what of that? We must have perseverance and above all confidence in ourselves. We must believe that we are gifted for something and that this thing must be attained.', 1036, 0), (488870, 'No life''s worth more than any other, no sister worth less than any brother.', 21674, 0), (488871, 'Transformation is a process, and as life happens there are tons of ups and downs. It''s a journey of discovery - there are moments on mountaintops and moments in deep valleys of despair.', 710, 0), (488872, 'Be willing to step outside your comfort zone once in a while; take the risks in life that seem worth taking. The ride might not be as predictable if you''d just planted your feet and stayed put, but it will be a heck of a lot more interesting.', 66840, 0), (488873, 'I don''t regret what I''ve been through. I''ve had ups and downs, super highs and some really low lows. I''ve been so blessed that I could never say, ''I wish this didn''t happen.'' It''s part of who I am. There''s nothing in my life that''s so ugh.', 24514, 0), (488874, 'Authenticity is everything! You have to wake up every day and look in the mirror, and you want to be proud of the person who''s looking back at you. And you can only do that if you''re being honest with yourself and being a person of high character. You have an opportunity every single day to write that story of your life.', 68228, 0), (488875, 'There is nothing I can do to undo what I did. I can only say again how sorry I am to those I let down and then strive to go forward with a greater sense of humility and purpose, and with gratitude to those who stood with me during a very difficult chapter in my life.', 68916, 0), (488876, 'Life is too short to worry about anything. You had better enjoy it because the next day promises nothing.', 67095, 0), (488877, 'One of the luckiest things that can happen to you in life is, I think, to have a happy childhood.', 94, 0), (488878, 'We cannot always control everything that happens to us in this life, but we can control how we respond. Many struggles come as problems and pressures that sometimes cause pain. Others come as temptations, trials, and tribulations.', 55804, 0), (488879, 'I think it''s important to find the little things in everyday life that make you happy.', 72299, 0), (488880, 'Loneliness is my least favorite thing about life. The thing that I''m most worried about is just being alone without anybody to care for or someone who will care for me.', 67062, 0), (488881, 'Instead of trying to make your life perfect, give yourself the freedom to make it an adventure, and go ever upward.', 69857, 0), (488882, 'My daughter is my biggest achievement. She is a little star and my life has changed so much for the better since she came along.', 73865, 0), (488883, 'The happiest moment of my life was probably when my daughter was born.', 54756, 0), (488884, 'In school, you''re taught a lesson and then given a test. In life, you''re given a test that teaches you a lesson.', 60, 0), (488885, 'The sky is always there for me, while my life has been going through many, many changes. When I look up the sky, it gives me a nice feeling, like looking at an old friend.', 1121, 0), (488886, 'My whole life is about winning. I don''t lose often. I almost never lose.', 64643, 0), (488887, 'I wish my school days could have dragged on a little longer, or that I could go back and do it later in life.', 68038, 0), (488888, 'The value of life is not in its duration, but in its donation. You are not important because of how long you live, you are important because of how effective you live.', 11162, 0), (488889, 'Without deep reflection one knows from daily life that one exists for other people.', 104, 0), (488890, 'You learn more about life from watching ''Big Brother'' than from reading a book.', 71933, 0), (488891, 'The game of life is a lot like football. You have to tackle your problems, block your fears, and score your points when you get the opportunity.', 60319, 0), (488892, 'It''s the game of life. Do I win or do I lose? One day they''re gonna shut the game down. I gotta have as much fun and go around the board as many times as I can before it''s my turn to leave.', 1097, 0), (488893, 'Wherever you are, be there totally. If you find your here and now intolerable and it makes you unhappy, you have three options: remove yourself from the situation, change it, or accept it totally. If you want to take responsibility for your life, you must choose one of those three options, and you must choose now. Then accept the consequences.', 378, 0), (488894, 'Life isn''t black and white. It''s a million gray areas, don''t you find?', 68428, 0), (488895, 'Going by my past journey, I am not certain where life will take me, what turns and twists will happen; nobody knows where they will end up. As life changes direction, I''ll flow with it.', 66894, 0), (488896, 'Everyone is handed adversity in life. No one''s journey is easy. It''s how they handle it that makes people unique.', 75657, 0), (488897, 'Live life for the moment because everything else is uncertain!', 12979, 0), (488898, 'Relax! Life is beautiful!', 68049, 0), (488899, 'Our prime purpose in this life is to help others. And if you can''t help them, at least don''t hurt them.', 5025, 0), (488900, 'The sole meaning of life is to serve humanity.', 93, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (488901, 'I used to think that the worst thing in life was to end up alone. It''s not. The worst thing in life is to end up with people who make you feel alone.', 2185, 0), (488902, 'My personal ambition remains the same - to be creative, to be modern, to stay one step ahead, to enjoy life.', 66890, 0), (488903, 'Life is a difficult game. You can win it only by retaining your birthright to be a person.', 1798, 0), (488904, 'No water, no life. No blue, no green.', 67053, 0), (488905, 'Do what you need to do and enjoy life as it happens.', 4764, 0), (488906, 'I''m actually pretty shy in real life. But I guess in front of the camera, I focus.', 67630, 0), (488907, 'Don''t ever doubt yourselves or waste a second of your life. It''s too short, and you''re too special.', 52532, 0), (488908, 'Life is what happens while you are busy making other plans.', 46, 0), (488909, 'Life is short, and it is up to you to make it sweet.', 68149, 0), (488910, 'Life''s tragedy is that we get old too soon and wise too late.', 1077, 0), (488911, 'Weddings are important because they celebrate life and possibility.', 67062, 0), (488912, 'Life is a series of waves to be embraced and overcome.', 66636, 0), (488913, 'Be thou the rainbow in the storms of life. The evening beam that smiles the clouds away, and tints tomorrow with prophetic ray.', 62558, 0), (488914, 'Life ain''t always beautiful, but it''s a beautiful ride.', 70210, 0), (488915, 'Common sense would suggest that having ability, like being smart, inspires confidence. It does, but only while the going is easy. The deciding factor in life is how you handle setbacks and challenges. People with a growth mindset welcome setbacks with open arms.', 68087, 0), (488916, 'Into each life some rain must fall.', 147, 0), (488917, 'You just got with the flow because life is just all about how you feel.', 70208, 0), (488918, 'Give yourself a gift of five minutes of contemplation in awe of everything you see around you. Go outside and turn your attention to the many miracles around you. This five-minute-a-day regimen of appreciation and gratitude will help you to focus your life in awe.', 21729, 0), (488919, 'I always say that the times in my life when I''ve been happiest are the times when I''ve seen, like, a sunset.', 23824, 0), (488920, 'The hardest thing in life to learn is which bridge to cross and which to burn.', 12531, 0), (488921, 'There is a tide in the affairs of men, Which taken at the flood, leads on to fortune. Omitted, all the voyage of their life is bound in shallows and in miseries. On such a full sea are we now afloat. And we must take the current when it serves, or lose our ventures.', 13, 0), (488922, 'I''m just going to go live life. I''m going to go enjoy life. I have nothing left to hide. I am kind of a free person, a free soul.', 67828, 0), (488923, 'Caring - about people, about things, about life - is an act of maturity.', 6023, 0), (488924, 'Don''t walk through life just playing football. Don''t walk through life just being an athlete. Athletics will fade. Character and integrity and really making an impact on someone''s life, that''s the ultimate vision, that''s the ultimate goal - bottom line.', 45107, 0), (488925, 'Everyone and everything that shows up in our life is a reflection of something that is happening inside of us.', 4680, 0), (488926, 'Life is a journey. When we stop, things don''t go right.', 6248, 0), (488927, 'Life is a journey and it''s about growing and changing and coming to terms with who and what you are and loving who and what you are.', 75658, 0), (488928, 'The purpose of our lives is to be happy.', 5025, 0), (488929, 'However difficult life may seem, there is always something you can do and succeed at.', 1222, 0), (488930, 'Negative emotions like loneliness, envy, and guilt have an important role to play in a happy life; they''re big, flashing signs that something needs to change.', 3243, 0), (488931, '