ped smiling when I got into fashion. Fashion stole my smile!', 67831, 0), (489327, 'Standing as a witness in all things means being kind in all things, being the first to say hello, being the first to smile, being the first to make the stranger feel a part of things, being helpful, thinking of others'' feelings, being inclusive.', 70311, 0), (489328, 'Great men show politeness in a particular way; a smile suffices to assure you that you are welcome, and keep about their avocations as if you were a member of the family.', 13434, 0), (489329, 'It''s so hard not to smile.', 847, 0), (489330, 'The catch phrase for the day is ''Do an act of kindness. Help one person smile.''', 75670, 0), (489331, 'And if you see me, smile and maybe give me a hug. That''s important to me too.', 756, 0), (489332, 'Smile at a stranger. See what happens.', 75671, 0), (489333, 'Never a lip is curved with pain that can''t be kissed into smiles again.', 10748, 0), (489334, 'I have a nice smile, pretty lips, and big round cheeks. They help me look like a teenager.', 66490, 0), (489335, 'She felt like a chess player who, by the clever handling of his pieces, sees the game taking the course intended. Her eyes were bright and tender with a smile as they glanced up into his; and her lips looked hungry for the kiss which they invited.', 6587, 0), (489336, 'I think I''ve always had a certain amount of skepticism of this whole ''shut up and smile'' theory. I haven''t ever swallowed that pill so easily, although I tried.', 52565, 0), (489337, 'Power doesn''t back up in the face of a smile, or in the face of a threat of some kind of nonviolent loving action. It''s not the nature of power to back up in the face of anything but some more power.', 1730, 0), (489338, 'We smile at the ignorance of the savage who cuts down the tree in order to reach its fruit but the same blunder is made by every person who is over eager and impatient in the pursuit of pleasure. ', 3573, 0), (489339, 'And the smile that is worth the praises of earth is the smile that shines through tears.', 541, 0), (489340, 'They might not need me but they might. I''ll let my head be just in sight a smile as small as mine might be precisely their necessity. ', 91, 0), (489341, 'Laughter is day, and sobriety is night; a smile is the twilight that hovers gently between both, more bewitching than either.', 2175, 0), (489342, 'To smile at the jest which plants a thorn in another''s breast is to become a principal in the mischief.', 20698, 0), (489343, 'I''ve never wanted anybody to like me because I had long hair or short hair, or that they liked the way I dressed or they liked the way I dressed or they liked the way I smile.', 52281, 0), (489344, 'Winning the World Cup was very special because it meant so much to so many. One thing about our country that is constant is cricket. The smile it brought to people''s faces was the thing I shall always remember. It reminded me, reminded all of us, of our importance to the lives of the Indian people less lucky than we are.', 69702, 0), (489345, 'You have to promote yourself you have to have this smile on your face all the time and be this nice guy - which I am! ', 16108, 0), (489346, 'When you smile, you don''t only appear to be more likable and courteous, you appear to be more competent.', 75672, 0), (489347, 'Not by appointment do we meet delight Or joy they heed not our expectancy But round some corner of the streets of life they of a sudden greet us with a smile. ', 62713, 0), (489348, 'A smile is a facelift that''s in everyone''s price range!', 64235, 0), (489349, 'I feel like a little kid who just walked into a candy store. I think that''s something to smile about.', 5945, 0), (489350, 'Breathing in, I am aware of my heart. Breathing out, I smile to my heart and know that my heart still functions normally. I feel grateful for my heart.', 69092, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489351, 'A tip for looking ''picture perfect'' is probably a smile. I think everyone looks better when they are happy you give off a glow - or at least that is what my mum would say! ', 70327, 0), (489352, 'Each one of us can do a good deed, every day and everywhere. In hospitals in desperate need of volunteers, in homes for the elderly where our parents and grandparents are longing for a smile, a listening ear, in the street, in our workplaces and especially at home.', 66578, 0), (489353, 'Once every lunar eclipse, you should be able to see me smile!', 71586, 0), (489354, 'I don''t know what I would have done without believing in God. His support gives me power and energy to continue to be optimistic, to smile, not to be depressed. Sometimes, if things are not going so well, I don''t cry. I say maybe it''s meant to be.', 75673, 0), (489355, 'She gave me a smile I could feel in my hip pocket.', 1016, 0), (489356, 'You know, I''ve got wrinkles on my forehead and smile lines, but what''s wrong with that? I love to smile.', 883, 0), (489357, 'The bat is gone, but the smile remains.', 72203, 0), (489358, 'When I see people laughing at ideas and companies we have backed, I smile. It means we are going to make a lot of money on that investment.', 69489, 0), (489359, 'It is impossible to persuade a man who does not disagree, but smiles.', 3292, 0), (489360, 'The company of fools may first make us smile, but in the end we always feel melancholy.', 2204, 0), (489361, 'I want to touch the heart of the world and make it smile.', 1280, 0), (489362, 'I think that anybody that smiles automatically looks better.', 67021, 0), (489363, 'I''ve always spent more time with a smile on my face than not, but the thing is, I don''t write about it.', 68214, 0), (489364, 'It takes a man to suffer ignorance and smile.', 9151, 0), (489365, 'One of the most important responsibilities in the Christian life is to care about others, smile at them, and be a friend to the friendless.', 22081, 0), (489366, 'Get up and dance, get up and smile, get up and drink to the days that are gone in the shortest while.', 75674, 0), (489367, 'We may smile at these matters, but they are melancholy illustrations.', 65168, 0), (489368, 'You see, with me, when I''m nervous, I smile and laugh.', 68094, 0), (489369, 'Well, there''s nothing more touching than putting a smile on a kid''s face when you can.', 61453, 0), (489370, 'Some people say they have a thirst for life. They''re excited about every day and they''re prepared to look the bad and the good straight in the face and greet it all with a smile. I like to think I''m one of those people.', 67708, 0), (489371, 'I don''t think I was a good model. I think I was born to emote and act. I would walk down the ramp and smile and they used to say, ''Give us a blank look.'' It was really difficult not to smile.', 66951, 0), (489372, 'Grit your teeth and smile. In the face of adversity, go. They don''t deserve you.', 66813, 0), (489373, 'As cheesy as it sounds, nothing beats a smile and a bit of confidence! As long as you feel good on the inside, you can still look beautiful without any makeup at all.', 847, 0), (489374, 'The pilgrim is humble and devout, and human, and charitable, and ready to smile and admire; therefore, he should comprehend the whole of his way, the people in it, and the hills and the clouds, and the habits of the various cities.', 4439, 0), (489375, 'Comrades, this man has a nice smile, but he''s got iron teeth.', 75675, 0), (489376, 'I hoped I could make people smile and laugh and have a good time.', 3675, 0), (489377, 'You get somebody to crack a smile, that''s a beautiful thing.', 68238, 0), (489378, 'The last time I saw Ted Kennedy was a generation after my first meeting, at the Senate subway below the Capitol on Obama''s Inauguration Day. He was his usual gregarious and gracious self - with beaming smile and booming voice wishing my husband and me good luck with our pregnancy and expressing his excitement about the new president.', 68044, 0), (489379, 'When we run out of them upstairs, I''ve been known to appropriate some from our greenroom, pocketing a few with one hand as I smile and greet our guests with the other. One time, Dave Zinczenko of ''Eat this, Not That!'' fame, busted me in the act. The cookies apparently fall in the ''not that'' category. I made a note of it.', 70449, 0), (489380, 'Most babies know how to win us over. We cannot help but smile at them and watch them smile back.', 66982, 0), (489381, 'It hurts when you have to smile and you don''t want to smile, but the best thing to do is to smile.', 47442, 0), (489382, 'There are just some really beautiful people in the world. When you''re walking down the street, or you''re at a restaurant, someone catches your eye because they have their own look. It goes way beyond what they''re wearing - into their mannerisms, the way they smile, or just the way they hold themselves.', 66806, 0), (489383, 'For me, relationship is very important. I can lose money, but I cannot lose a relationship. The test is, at the end of a conversation or a negotiation, both must smile.', 73400, 0), (489384, 'As a former waitress myself, I know firsthand how a simple smile from someone can improve your day and how a single harsh word can destroy it. Being courteous and thoughtful costs you nothing and can sometimes pay you dividends in unexpected ways.', 1351, 0), (489385, 'I had the opportunity to go into the hospitals and talk to kids and see a kid and make him smile. Why? Because I''m a special person? No. It had nothing to do with that. It has everything to do with me being the quarterback at the University of Florida. And to not take advantage of that is a shame.', 4052, 0), (489386, 'My new dressing goal is to make little kids and babies smile at all the bright, clashing colours I can wear at once. It makes me laugh when I catch sight of my own reflection - life is too short not have fun!', 67148, 0), (489387, 'Nothing can resist the person who smiles at life - I don''t mean the ironic and disillusioned smile of my grandfather, but the triumphant smile of the person who knows that he will survive, or that at least he will be saved by what seems to be destroying him.', 531, 0), (489388, 'Every bit of joy in my heart, you know, every smile on my face is yours. It''s awesome to be able to share that with somebody.', 70256, 0), (489389, 'I still don''t love the darkness, though I''ve learned to smile in it a little bit, now and then.', 22849, 0), (489390, 'I made a circle with a smile for a mouth on yellow paper, because it was sunshiny and bright.', 75670, 0), (489391, 'What looks like enjoyment is the sneer of contempt. That''s not a smile.', 7905, 0), (489392, 'As long as you smile, have sparkly eyes and stick your shoulders back, nobody''s going to notice your bum or your waist or your feet, for that matter.', 70698, 0), (489393, 'When you''re walking down the street, or you''re at a restaurant, someone catches your eye because they have their own look. It goes way beyond what they''re wearing - into their mannerisms, the way they smile, or just the way they hold themselves.', 66806, 0), (489394, 'Ever since I was four years old, I loved making people smile, making them think, making them feel good, feel some kind of emotion.', 75676, 0), (489395, 'I definitely want to continue working in independent films - and big budget stuff as well - but there''s a freedom you have when you''re not getting paid. It''s easier to say no and there''s no pressure to please the powers that be. Also I don''t have to hear ''flirt and smile more.''', 74579, 0), (489396, 'On ''America''s Top Model,'' I''ve always told my girls to smile with their eyes. We call it ''smizing.'' Over the years, it''s actually become part of pop culture. I would be walking down the street, and girls would say, ''Smize!''', 1725, 0), (489397, 'After my husband John Lennon passed away, I tried to smile for my health.', 1121, 0), (489398, 'For me, fragrances are very - one of these beautiful art forms that bring about a whole host of things. It''s what you want to smell like, it''s memories that make you smile or are resonant of times in your life, it can remind you of music. If you''re a lover of scent, it''s a very kind of particular and evocative thing.', 12497, 0), (489399, 'God blessed me with two unbelievable parents, and I am just like both of them. I have the smile and charisma of my mother and the big heart of my mom, because she wants to save the world and help the world, so I am just like her.', 67024, 0), (489400, 'It''s sort of a feeling of power onstage. It''s really the ability to make people smile, or just to turn them one way or another for that duration of time, and for it to have some effect later on. I don''t really think it''s power... it''s the goodness.', 22771, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489401, 'I think music, in my opinion, is not about motivation in the way it''s - it''s not a running base. It''s art. And my whole philosophy of music is different. It''s almost like cooking and serving to people, seeing them smile and enjoying the food, really.', 66442, 0), (489402, 'There are certain expectations that are put on you as a child actor, but mainly it''s just turn up and say your lines with a lot of energy and a cute smile.', 72950, 0), (489403, 'Don''t let people see when you''re mad - just smile and laugh.', 69315, 0), (489404, 'We should celebrate how amazing our bodies are! We all have things that we like and dislike about our bodies, but we need to focus on what we love - maybe it''s a great smile, strong legs or curly hair?', 67138, 0), (489405, 'It scares you: all the noise, the rattling, the shaking. But the look on everybody''s face when you''re finished and packing, it''s the best smile in the world; and there''s nobody hurt, and the well''s under control.', 67711, 0), (489406, 'Let me smile with the wise, and feed with the rich.', 2087, 0), (489407, 'Usually, if you smile at them and show some interest in the toy, they will give it to you. That''s a straight up Democrat move!', 2324, 0), (489408, 'I retire with a smile on my face, in good health, and ready to spend autumns at my kids'' games instead of my own. I''m excited to start the next chapter of my life.', 75677, 0), (489409, 'It is boorish to live ungraciously: the giving is the hardest part what does it cost to add a smile? ', 5879, 0), (489410, 'I have two rules for a great book: make me think and make me smile.', 14960, 0), (489411, 'I truly believe my job is to make sure people smile.', 7162, 0), (489412, 'I like to smile. I smile even when I''m nervous since it calms me down and shows my friendliness.', 66879, 0), (489413, 'Joy''s smile is much closer to tears than laughter.', 98, 0), (489414, 'If the Starbucks secret is a smile when you get your latte... ours is that the Web site adapts to the individual''s taste.', 70021, 0), (489415, 'To you wives who are constantly complaining and see only the dark side of life, and feel that you are unloved and unwanted, look into your own hearts and minds. If there is something wrong, turn about. Put a smile on your faces. Make yourselves more attractive. Brighten your outlook.', 197, 0), (489416, 'I wake up every day with a smile on my face.', 75678, 0), (489417, 'A smile is the chosen vehicle of all ambiguities.', 2584, 0), (489418, 'Thinking about your training should put a smile on your face. As cliche as it sounds, you are worth all the time and energy you''ve put in. Unleash your emotions with a cheer, or even a signature roar, after a tough workout.', 67751, 0), (489419, 'We are entertainers. We have to give our audience a good time. If my name serves that purpose, if that brings a smile on your face, then I think it is good and my job has been done.', 69360, 0), (489420, 'A stale article, if you dip it in a good, warm, sunny smile, will go off better than a fresh one that you''ve scowled upon.', 650, 0), (489421, 'If you''re able to help some people and make them smile and make them realize that life is good, then that''s worth so much more than buying a pair of shoes.', 68355, 0), (489422, 'I think it''s really important that I''m not the only model in the world that goes through personal problems. People forget that we''re human. We don''t get to call in sick. You have to go and put on a smile. Every single day is a first impression, so you can''t have a bummed-out day.', 60670, 0), (489423, 'I''m not the athlete I was when I was training for the Olympics in ''92 or when I was working out every single day. I have to live in moderation: I work out three or four days a week, and I smile while I''m working out - I really do enjoy it. I work out with my girlfriends and make it a social competition.', 67751, 0), (489424, '''Tis easy enough to be pleasant, When life flows along like a song; But the man worth while is the one who will smile when everything goes dead wrong.', 541, 0), (489425, 'There are those who believe that the value of a children''s book can be measured only in terms of the moral lessons it tries to impose or the perfect role models it offers. Personally, I happen to think that a book is of extraordinary value if it gives the reader nothing more than a smile or two. In fact, I happen to think that''s huge.', 47221, 0), (489426, 'Acting is a sense of wonder and magic and mystery for me and when life takes me on a new journey, I simply remember the smile my first ballet recital put on my face and I move forward.', 74837, 0), (489427, 'Mind you, physical training doesn''t necessarily mean going to an expert for advice. One doesn''t have to make a mountain out of a molehill. Get out in the fresh air and walk briskly - and don''t forget to wear a smile while you''re at it. Don''t over-do. Take it easy at first and build on your effort day by day.', 71947, 0), (489428, 'I don''t smile as much as I should, even though I smile inside a lot.', 285, 0), (489429, 'Obama''s stern demeanor punctuated by intermittent flashes of his wide, relaxing smile is his greatest weapon in defusing pent-up angst.', 18085, 0), (489430, 'I get accused of having a haughty smugness. I have a lopsided mouth. I can''t help it. I was born with it. It looks as if I am smirking. I have had my publicist tell me, ''Don''t do that smile on the red carpet.'' I''m, like, ''That''s my smile.''', 69331, 0), (489431, 'Giving back is the right thing to do, whether it''s donating clothing or even just a smile to someone who needs it.', 70213, 0), (489432, 'I''ve just got a really bad smile. I go for the scowl instead.', 68421, 0), (489433, 'You learn to laugh at yourself, and you also lean on comedy as a crutch to kind of take the edge off because comedians often are self-deprecating, and they cross lines that they shouldn''t. Stuff like that brings a smile to my face every once in a while when needed.', 38715, 0), (489434, 'Have you seen these Japanese hospital droids, or humanoids, or whatever they call it? They''ve perfected the skin, and the skin looks so real. They have these motors between the eyes for when they smile. It''s just mind-blowing.', 68236, 0), (489435, 'The man who can smile when things go wrong has thought of someone else he can blame it on.', 1894, 0), (489436, 'A smile abroad is often a scowl at home.', 63203, 0), (489437, 'Youth smiles without any reason. It is one of its chiefest charms.', 54002, 0), (489438, 'We sometimes laugh from ear to ear, but it would be impossible for a smile to be wider than the distance between our eyes.', 21982, 0), (489439, 'Right now, I''m following the Buddhist principle: Smile as abuse is hurled your way and this too shall pass.', 68393, 0), (489440, 'Allowing yourself to smile takes 99% of the effort.', 75679, 0), (489441, 'But with exquisite breathing you smile, with satisfaction of love, And I touch you again as you tick in the silence and settle in sleep.', 75680, 0), (489442, 'Some people know that they are so adorable looking, all they have to do is smile and dress up and they get plenty from that. Then there are some of us who, early on, see that that doesn''t work. So we joke about it.', 52069, 0), (489443, 'If you want to meet a woman, it''s best just to smile and say hi.', 72881, 0), (489444, 'Laughter is regional: a smile extends over the whole face.', 21982, 0), (489445, 'I''m as happy a man as any in the world, for the whole world seems to smile upon me!', 7329, 0), (489446, 'There is not a soul who does not have to beg alms of another, either a smile, a handshake, or a fond eye.', 63500, 0), (489447, 'People always say golfers don''t smile. But there is so much psychology in golf so we have to be a bit robotic.', 68523, 0), (489448, 'I just want to make people smile.', 2033, 0), (489449, 'If you force yourself to smile, within a couple minutes, you feel happy.', 75681, 0), (489450, 'Just because a situation is grim doesn''t mean you don''t have every right to smile.', 18940, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489451, 'I always said that if I could just find a guy who could chop wood and had a nice smile, it wouldn''t bother me if he was a thug or an aristocrat, as long as he was a good guy. And I''ve ended up with an educated thug.', 66980, 0), (489452, 'If I''m a bad mood, I can''t go on stage and smile.', 72592, 0), (489453, 'There is no greater feeling in business than building a product which impacts people''s lives in a profound way. When we look around at the thousands of people who have attended Summit gatherings, it makes us smile to see the new friendships, business partnerships and philanthropic initiatives that each event produces.', 75682, 0), (489454, 'Sometimes you say things with a smile with the precise intention of making it clear that you are not being serious, and are only kidding. If I salute a friend with a smile and say, ''How are you, you old scoundrel!'' clearly I don''t really mean he''s a scoundrel.', 736, 0), (489455, 'I think a smile can make your whole body. Models, they look fabulous, but they don''t smile, and they look so mad.', 70497, 0), (489456, 'If women had to promise to provide for a man for a lifetime before he removed his veil and showed her his smile, would we think of this as a system of female privilege?', 18071, 0), (489457, 'I am generally a very happy and easygoing person. I also believe it''s always better to meet people with a smile rather than looking cold, especially when you first meet. It changes everything.', 69264, 0), (489458, 'I try to keep people happy. I go out of my way to get a smile. That''s the way my mother raised me.', 75683, 0), (489459, 'I eat every two hours. I sleep for eight hours. I have lots of water. I pray to keep calm. Most importantly, I have a smile on my face.', 69080, 0), (489460, 'Even a smile is a good deed.', 66578, 0), (489461, 'There''s nothing like seeing the smile on my kids'' faces. Laughing together. Playing. It''s the best.', 13187, 0), (489462, 'As a female, you are often being asked by directors to be warmer, softer, flirt more, smile more etc... None of those things are bad, and obviously we are capable of a variety of human behavior, but it gets really old having to play into somebody''s stereotype or ideal.', 74579, 0), (489463, 'If you cannot smile when you listen to music, then do not listen to it!', 69213, 0), (489464, 'More people smile at me now I''m richer.', 67778, 0), (489465, 'Once you don''t smile on film, they say, ''Let''s have that bloke who doesn''t smile.''', 69193, 0), (489466, 'Y''know, smile, dance, get crazy... we sure do while we''re making it, because music is our leeezshure; it''s my fun.', 75684, 0), (489467, 'No matter what I put out, somebody will be offended. I made a video on 10 reasons to smile, and it has dislikes. That should be an indication that there will be some who get offended no matter what you do. The best you can do as an entertainer or as someone who performs is to follow what you believe in.', 68220, 0), (489468, '''Chef'' is a dish of arroz con pollo served with a smile but not much style. The critic in the film would give it a low grade, for agreeability without ambition.', 67854, 0), (489469, 'Not everything is going to be handed to you just because you''re talented with a big smile. Sometimes you just gotta get out and shoot jumpers for hours and hours and hours. That''s something I didn''t really get a grasp on until way later, waking up early and treating it like a job if you''re serious about it. Get the freak up and, you know, work.', 68880, 0), (489470, 'People want to start their day off with a smile or, better yet, a guffaw.', 45192, 0), (489471, 'Pictorial is something that I am not used to. You have to pose, smile, bend your arm, straighten up, look to the left.', 70690, 0), (489472, 'When onstage, I always try to take my audience through as many emotions as I possibly can. I want them to go from laughter to tears, be shocked and surprised and walk out the door with a renewed sense of themselves - and maybe a smile.', 1356, 0), (489473, 'No, I like to wear as least amount of makeup as I can during my everyday life because I''m just all about keeping my skin healthy and hydrated and I love to laugh and have a great time and smile - that''s when I feel the most pretty so I just want to make sure that I stay happy.', 47780, 0), (489474, 'Smiles come naturally to me, but I started thinking of them as an art form at my command. I studied all the time. I looked at magazines, I''d practice in front of the mirror and I''d ask photographers about the best angles. I can now pull out a smile at will.', 1725, 0), (489475, 'If what I have to do is share a sandwich to lift someone''s spirits, put a smile on their face - the worst thing that happens is I go broke!', 67848, 0), (489476, 'I am so happy to be alive. That''s the one thing I''d like for people to know. Sometimes people walk by and slip up and say the wrong thing about me, and I''ll smile. They wonder why am I smiling. Because I''m happy that I''m alive.', 26132, 0), (489477, 'When I take my kids out for dinner or lunch, people smile at us.', 536, 0), (489478, 'I come from a place where everything about me, even my body language, is saying: I mean you no harm. I smile, I laugh. Basic stuff for most people.', 75685, 0), (489479, 'Advice from my experience, for me, I''ve never taken no as an answer, I don''t believe in that. If I want something, I''m going to get it. When people tell me that I can''t do something, it just motivates me more. For me, it makes me smile, because I just want to prove everybody wrong.', 69724, 0), (489480, 'I''ve had more ups than downs in my career. All you can do is keep working. You still have to take enjoyment out of what you''re doing, and things will turn, and my smile has always been there. In good moments and bad.', 67768, 0), (489481, 'There are so many beautiful things that are a part of the world, and I''ve always looked at life that way; I''ve always tried to put on a smile and a brave front, not just for my kids but in my own life and all the difficulties that I''ve gone through.', 64979, 0), (489482, 'Everything about ''UY'' is new and fresh, and we are extremely happy at the response from the audiences, as most people are walking out of cinema halls with a smile on their faces.', 72134, 0), (489483, 'If you walk down the street and smile at someone, that will get passed on to the next person. That has the power to change someone''s day.', 69053, 0), (489484, 'With my father and sister being very depressed for most of their lives, it was incumbent on me to try to make them laugh, in this ridiculous way. They were the wittiest people I knew, but to get a smile from them was like winning the lottery.', 4222, 0), (489485, 'It''s important to maintain an attractive smile as you age. A lighter, less beige, more white tooth color is key, but no Chiclets.', 71889, 0), (489486, 'The smile of God is victory.', 997, 0), (489487, 'Reproof on her lip, but a smile in her eye.', 12187, 0), (489488, 'Generally, when a record label suggests album ideas for you, you smile politely, and then proceed to shoot it down, because it''s never what you as an artist feel is right for you.', 75686, 0), (489489, 'When you walk into a room, a healthy, beautiful smile is incredibly important.', 71908, 0), (489490, 'When I see myself on film it makes me smile, I mean making a good living doing what I enjoy is soo much fun. I just hope that everyone has the chance to enjoy life like I do.', 38202, 0), (489491, 'Go, forget me - why should sorrow, O''er that brow a shadow fling? Go, forget me - and tomorrow, brightly smile and sweetly sing. Smile - though I shall not be near thee; Sing - though I shall never hear thee.', 75687, 0), (489492, 'We ought to be beating our chests every day. We ought to look in the mirror, stick out our chests, suck in our bellies, and say, ''Damn, we''re Americans,'' and smile.', 75688, 0), (489493, 'The truth is that when Lennon is Bosephus, she is so mean to me. She can''t smile because the mustache will come off. So in between takes, it''s just scowling. And then when we are on camera, Bosephus treats me like a piece of meat. I''m repulsed and also attracted to it.', 68227, 0), (489494, 'Sometimes people have questioned whether I was making fun of the industry or just at myself. I''m just trying to raise a smile. Clothes aren''t meant to be worshipped at a church altar.', 38405, 0), (489495, 'At one time, you could sit on the Rue de la Paix in Paris or at the Habima Theater in Tel Aviv or in Medina and you could see a person come in, black, white, it didn''t matter. You said, ''That''s an American'' because there''s a readiness to smile and to talk to people.', 74, 0), (489496, '''SMiLE'' is perhaps the Beach Boys'' most legendary album. It was recorded in 1966 and 1967 but only saw a formal release in 2011. That''s a long time to wait for what was said to be Brian Wilson''s masterpiece.', 68, 0), (489497, 'A bland smile is like a green light at an intersection, it feels good when you get one, but you forget it the moment you''re past it.', 1002, 0), (489498, 'We''ve all met those who seem to radiate happiness. They seem to smile more than others they laugh more than others - just being around them makes us happier as well. ', 4294, 0), (489499, 'Jesus wept Voltaire smiled. From that divine tear and from that human smile is derived the grace of present civilization. ', 98, 0), (489500, 'I''ve learned to lose with a smile on my face. That''s what the Oscar teaches you.', 60783, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489501, 'I''m not this callous clown walking around laughing at life all the time. I''ve had some serious, serious problems in my life. But I''ve come out with a smile.', 14227, 0), (489502, 'So, my style has hopefully changed over the years and it is more relaxed, and I do tend to smile and have more than one expression these days hopefully - which I didn''t at the beginning.', 17159, 0), (489503, 'Sometimes when I''m being photographed, I hear the voice of this photographer who told me when I was about six while he was taking my school photo that I didn''t have a nice smile, and I shouldn''t smile in photos.', 69298, 0), (489504, 'I''ve told several writers this, and, again, I get back to it, but if you want to make God smile, tell him your plans.', 67364, 0), (489505, 'I would try to promote something that I loved, and the entire interview would be about my personal life. I would leave a room feeling defeated, feeling embarrassed, but I would always make sure to put that smile on my face because I wasn''t going to let them get to me.', 793, 0), (489506, 'I''m so envious of that genetic wiring that immediately puts a smile on your face. My genetic wiring just puts creases in my eyebrows.', 12497, 0), (489507, 'City Ballet has to develop choreographers of stature and a new approach to coaching before everything we value about it fades away and, in the great tradition of the Cheshire Cat, there''s nothing left but Peter Martins'' smile.', 20280, 0), (489508, 'I was talking to a guy who was holding his 18-month-old daughter with the only limb he had left, and he had a smile on his face. I thought, ''I''m not even a 10th of this man.''', 1252, 0), (489509, 'I have witnessed the softening of the hardest of hearts by a simple smile.', 1245, 0), (489510, 'A body smiles, like, 72 times a day. Where does that smile go? That''s what I want to know.', 1245, 0), (489511, 'In general, men are wired to notice obvious signs that convey interest in mating - a warm smile, for example - and ignore other subtleties, like if your lipstick is faded.', 52746, 0), (489512, 'It''s true that a smile can take years off a person - not that such a thing matters in Yoko Ono''s case.', 68243, 0), (489513, 'My children and my husband make me smile. My work makes me smile.', 67831, 0), (489514, 'I loved the Kennedy Center Honors because you just sit there, smile, wave, and cry.', 51091, 0), (489515, 'Let him who expects one class of society to prosper in the highest degree, while the other is in distress, try whether one side; of the face can smile while the other is pinched.', 1348, 0), (489516, 'Of course I used to smile and laugh in 1976, but not when I was competing. Please show me somebody who laughs when they are concentrating; I always smiled.', 14526, 0), (489517, 'I''m a happy guy. I just want to see people laugh and smile.', 68906, 0), (489518, 'I don''t smile a lot in my pictures. I''m always so... grim.', 23151, 0), (489519, 'I am so saddened and grossed out by young women who look like creepy, old aliens because of their new Barbie noses and lips. Is that a smile or a grimace?', 68919, 0), (489520, 'There''s an old adage about speakers: You won''t remember what they said, but you''ll never forget how they made you feel. Trump knows that in his bones. He gives his supporters - and they are growing - a terrific feeling of safety and security, along with a laugh and a smile.', 67833, 0), (489521, 'I never realized before this the emotional power of some really simple, corny tropes: people with top hats, people with batons, confetti going off, how important it is to smile.', 54808, 0), (489522, 'I hated the ballet, but I liked performing. I did 20 shows, and I couldn''t get the smile off my face.', 69335, 0), (489523, 'The very best hotel I''ve stayed in is the Intercontinental on Park Lane. We went there for the Chelsea Flower Show a few years ago, and it was sheer luxury. Everybody had a smile on their face. I came home and changed all my pillows because the hotel ones were so beautiful.', 43810, 0), (489524, 'Comedians like to see people smile. With acting, I love giving people a feeling, an emotion. I like to give people a feeling. When they come away from my scene, I want them to think.', 68249, 0), (489525, 'I feel like looking in the mirror when you brush your teeth, yes, I see lines, and then I smile and I see things here and there. But that''s just, you know, you - that''s your journey, you know?', 69264, 0), (489526, 'When I came into office, people said, ''Billionaire? How do they live? What do they eat? How do they sleep?'' Today, they see me on the subway coming uptown. A couple of people say hi, some people smile and nod. Some people just sleep. It''s not an issue.', 67699, 0), (489527, 'I''ve been dealing with the press for 45 years. You need a very long spoon to sup with them. While you are always grateful, they are like badly trained dogs. They smile and wag and bite your arm off.', 67643, 0), (489528, 'Our aim is to develop affectionate robots that can make people smile.', 70056, 0), (489529, 'I have a few go-to moves like jazz hands, shake the booty, stupid eyes. It was once a mating ritual, but now it''s all about looking silly and making the kids smile.', 75142, 0), (489530, 'Actors are supposed to be these runaways that get in a covered wagon filled with hats and tambourines and go from town to town making people smile.', 75142, 0), (489531, 'I''m all about people that appreciate, that are grateful, that smile, that have a sense of humour - the dirtier the laugh, the better- that''s my kind of vibe... and I hope that''s the kind of thing that I attract.', 69238, 0), (489532, 'As a New Yorker, this is what you do: you confront, jab, and slap, sometimes wrongly, then smile and forget about it.', 10679, 0), (489533, 'I always remember this neighbor who would ask me to babysit for her. She looked like Jayne Mansfield, and I remember babysitting for, like, five hours and she would pay me 80 cents, with a phony smile. I used to go home fuming to my mum.', 69342, 0), (489534, 'When men have a smile on their faces, that does a lot for me.', 69343, 0), (489535, 'If you can''t relax during your interview, then nothing you do to prepare will matter. Being yourself is essential to the selection process, and interviewers will feel it if you''re too nervous. Showing fear or anxiety appears weak compared to a relaxed smile and genuine confidence.', 68087, 0), (489536, 'When I''m getting a chance to do my job or make somebody''s day, and be on stage where I love, and see all the fans having fun, you can''t help but smile.', 67360, 0), (489537, 'I am happy at Tottenham. I go into work every day with a smile on my face, and that is important.', 75689, 0), (489538, 'I have a great smile. A lot of people don''t know that.', 75690, 0), (489539, 'Scarlett Johansson has a smile she tries to suppress in every movie she makes. She''s been trying to keep a straight face since she appeared with Bill Murray 11 years ago in her breakthrough, ''Lost in Translation.''', 8777, 0), (489540, 'On the red carpet, one tip is to suck in your cheekbones - apparently it looks better on camera. I don''t know, though; I think a nice smile is best.', 70638, 0), (489541, 'Some people are fighting much, much more important battles and much bigger battles, and if we get the chance to put a smile on their face for ten seconds, it''s so worth it.', 75691, 0), (489542, 'I live to leave somebody with a positive experience when they''ve met me, and make someone smile for the day.', 75691, 0), (489543, 'Make people have a smile when they finish your e-mail.', 70057, 0), (489544, 'I''m honest and tell it like it is. I''ve been around the horn a few times and learned valuable lessons from screwing up a bit. So, if I can pass off advice or make someone smile on the way to work, I''m for it.', 72466, 0), (489545, 'No connection to the average voter - Clinton has an air of superiority. Despite her wide smile and pleasant appearance, she is envisioned as someone who is trying to hide something all the time.', 19591, 0), (489546, 'The NBA Schedule was made up by one man, Eddie Gottlieb, who had owned the Philadelphia Warriors. Eddie had a Buddha-like body and a crinkly smile, and because he had also been an owner in baseball''s old Negro leagues, he was known as the Mogul.', 72467, 0), (489547, 'Tears are sometimes an inappropriate response to death. When a life has been lived completely honestly, completely successfully, or just completely, the correct response to death''s perfect punctuation mark is a smile.', 28504, 0), (489548, 'I will tell you with 100 percent confidence, Jon Jones is not deep in my head. The fact he actually thinks that, it makes me smile every day.', 69733, 0), (489549, 'Every now and then, someone will tell me that one of my books has made them laugh out loud. I never believe them because: a.) my books don''t make me laugh out loud; and b.) sometimes I have said this to a writer, when really what I meant was, ''Your book made me smile appreciatively.''', 1554, 0), (489550, 'If you''re in my shoes, and your goal is to leave people with the biggest possible smile on their face, then doing the meet-and-greet afterwards makes sense.', 13941, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489551, 'Kanye is so much fun. He''s a wonderful person. What I love about Kim and Kanye is that I think they save their happy moments and their smiles for themselves rather than sharing everything with the public. And listen, when a camera is shoved in your face trying to take a selfie, you do not want to smile.', 67832, 0), (489552, 'As a model, I really stand for not being a model, if that makes sense. When I started, the whole idea of the model was very different; it was a bit stuck-up. Not stuck-up, but no one was trying to have fun, or not even have fun, but be willing to smile.', 68038, 0), (489553, 'I cry at anything remotely touching - smile at me warmly and I''m off... television also does it, everything from ''X-Factor'' to cereal commercials. I cry when I am tired. I also cry when I laugh.', 66890, 0), (489554, 'I guess the news is this: If you''re a Republican and you smile, liberals don''t like it. Maybe that''s because Democrats are afraid that I''ve been able to show an optimistic vision for this country.', 71296, 0), (489555, 'I''m a workhorse. I''ll take anything and everything I can get, and I''ll do it with a smile on my face.', 69724, 0), (489556, 'As I get older, I want to do more films for kids because they''re the best audience around. Just putting a smile on a kid''s face is the best thing.', 70221, 0), (489557, 'Later in my life, I''m going to look back and smile and be very fulfilled. I know that if I don''t give it my all right now I''ll regret it later. That''s very important to me, because I''ve worked all my life to have this.', 32889, 0), (489558, 'Clinton''s hands remain incredibly clean, don''t they, and Tony Blair''s smile remains as wide as ever. I view these guises with profound contempt.', 3174, 0), (489559, 'I get really frustrated if people don''t smile.', 70537, 0), (489560, 'Religion can emerge in all forms of feeling: here wild anger, there the sweetest pain; here consuming hatred, there the childlike smile of serene humility.', 68443, 0), (489561, 'I could be hit by a Sara Lee truck tomorrow. Which is not a bad way of going: ''Richard Simmons Found in a Freeway in Pound Cake and Fudge, With a Smile on His Face.'' Let''s face it. We don''t know anything.', 68273, 0), (489562, 'I will have my publicist pull pictures of the way I look at events so I can see, ''Oh, that cut is not as flattering as I thought,'' or ''I should smile bigger,'' or ''That positioning is odd.'' I learn from it.', 69740, 0), (489563, 'I think Led Zeppelin must have worn some of the most peculiar clothing that men had ever been seen to wear without cracking a smile.', 22771, 0), (489564, 'You know when someone''s over-flattering you in a way. You smile but you can''t believe it.', 10905, 0), (489565, 'I wish to be appreciated not only as a film star but also for the person I am. If I manage to bring a smile on people''s faces, then I think I''ll be successful.', 69743, 0), (489566, 'If you''re authentic, people smile because they sense there''s a piece of themselves there.', 12780, 0), (489567, 'My smile will always be broken, but I''ll always be grateful for the chance to get to do what I get to do.', 72123, 0), (489568, 'Somebody said to me, ''Whenever somebody says your name, a smile comes to their face.'' That''s a great accolade. I strive to keep it that way.', 70222, 0), (489569, 'My theory is, if you force yourself to smile enough, then you start to feel it. Which comes in handy all the time.', 69508, 0), (489570, 'Playing hard to get is not the way to win me over. I''m definitely more for the girl who can smile and laugh all the time and just have a good time!', 69198, 0), (489571, 'Julia Roberts taught me how to knit on the set of ''Mona Lisa Smile.''', 72716, 0), (489572, 'I was walking around legally blind. Now I have 20-20 vision. I can''t believe I spent so many years blurry, but I think that coincides with how I was feeling. Now I notice if people are watching me, but I also smile right back if someone waves, which helps.', 754, 0), (489573, 'I have always been a flirt. My mother says whe I was a child, I used to stand outside the house and just smile at everyone who walked by. Like, ''Please take me with you!''', 218, 0), (489574, 'I just feel like people like a little break. Especially at 12:37 at night, you go, like, ''I''m just tired of the snarky right now. I just want to lie down and have somebody make me laugh for an hour. Entertain me, and then I''m going to sleep with a smile on my face.'' That''s my job; that''s what I do.', 61859, 0), (489575, 'The coolest part about seeing a girl wear something comfortable is the smile that you can just feel coming through from inside her.', 53743, 0), (489576, 'The ''good'' mother, with her fixed smile, her rigidity, her goody-goody outlook, her obsession with unnecessary hygiene, is in fact a fool. It is the ''bad'' mother, unafraid of a joke and a glass of wine, richly self-expressive, scornful of suburban values, who is, in reality, good.', 7476, 0), (489577, 'I thought, ''It doesn''t matter what that woman is wearing,'' but then I realised actually it''s our job as designers to make women smile; to bring them the chocolate without the calories.', 68212, 0), (489578, 'For me, music makes my smile brighter during my workouts. It adds that extra something that motivates me to go further or work harder!', 67751, 0), (489579, 'We''ve been trained since kindergarten: Be nice, be kind, share, put on a smile. So we''re conditioned to squash our natural selfish instincts, and that''s the right thing for society.', 33509, 0), (489580, 'I used to watch some of the reality shows about models, and then, weirdly, now I try to incorporate into my fashion shoots the skills I learnt from watching those shows. It''s like, thanks Tyra, ''cause you''ve given me, like, all the cool tips. Like how to smile with your eyes.', 67065, 0), (489581, 'You know, there''s nothing like seeing the smile on my kids'' faces. Laughing together. Playing. It''s the best.', 13187, 0), (489582, 'I am trying to inspire people to just take control of their oral health, because if we don''t take care of our oral health, it affects so many different aspects of our lives. If your smile and mouth is not together, it affects your relationship, your self-esteem, your health.', 73210, 0), (489583, 'I played the violin my whole life. I wanted to play from the time I was just a little kid, and I''ve always loved dance as well. I wanted to make people smile. I wanted to add an extra energy to my playing and make it visual and make it unique and fun.', 22683, 0), (489584, 'It''s really hard to smile when you play. As a performer, if I ever find myself focusing, it''s like, ''Oh no - orchestra face!'' It''s not attractive at all, so I have to focus on smiling.', 22683, 0), (489585, 'While journalists cannot right every wrong, champion every cause or fix every problem, they can - through the written word - lift someone''s burden for a day, make some elderly woman on a bus smile or let them know they are noticed by someone.', 37774, 0), (489586, 'Sometimes Queens'' music is dark, but somehow it''s ok to deliver it with a smile on your face because thing''s are still going to kick in.', 20120, 0), (489587, 'Riding Valegro always makes you smile, so I enjoy it.', 68290, 0), (489588, 'I can''t help but smile when I ride Valegro; I think something, and he does it. I laugh, and I think, ''God, how does he know? I didn''t even ask. I just thought it.''', 68290, 0), (489589, 'It is spectacular. From about five minutes in, when we knew for sure that we were going to have the weather to go, the smile on my face just got bigger and bigger, and I was just beaming through the whole launch. I mean, it is just an amazing ride.', 2061, 0), (489590, 'My mother-in-law speaks not a word of English. I speak not a word of Tajiki. So I smile at her ingratiatingly and she fixes me with a beady eye.', 30001, 0), (489591, '''Priced to sell'' - just the phrase makes me smile. When a dealer says all the items in his booth are priced to sell, he means he''s tagged them as aggressively as he can to get you to buy them. Don''t worry, though, I still haggle. You have to. That''s the point of a flea market.', 69884, 0), (489592, 'I was never one of those surly teenagers who doesn''t smile. My lovely godfather said it was always lovely to see me because I was the only teenager who smiled. And I was so in awe of him, I thought it was one of the best things anyone had ever said to me. So it made me want to live up to what he said.', 71506, 0), (489593, 'In politics you learn to always smile.', 17581, 0), (489594, 'I''ve been successful in different areas, but nothing brings a smile to my face more than my oldest son, Zaire, and my second son, Zion, saying the kind word of ''Dad.''', 68367, 0), (489595, 'Young women from a very young age are taught that life will be easier if you can just turn on the charming smile and say very little and be complacent and docile and sweet.', 52565, 0), (489596, 'I love Jesus Christ with all my heart and everything He stands for. I think that sums up everything that I want for my life, everything I want for my family, everything I want for my career. I want it to be entertaining. I want people to smile and tap their toes, but I want it to be meaningful when the day is done.', 69758, 0), (489597, 'I''m quite British in the sense of not expressing my emotions much. I save it for my songs. If you ask about a death in the family, or a lover, I will not be emotional. I''d probably answer with a smile. Because that''s what we British blokes do.', 16022, 0), (489598, 'I have learned to smile when I wasn''t happy, to sing when I didn''t feel like it, and to do things just to please my fans.', 67074, 0), (489599, 'People relate to me, and I try to make songs that make people smile.', 68956, 0), (489600, 'When I hear theists and atheists pontificating on how they know God does or does not exist, I can only smile at the irrationality and, yes, vanity of the notion.', 50450, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489601, 'The Oscars are a lot different when you are a nominee. You walk around with this big smile on your face, and everyone, even people who work for rival film companies, tells you they voted for you.', 31112, 0), (489602, 'A man can be drawn across the room with the simplicity of a smile. That''s why your pearly whites should always be straight and shiny. I think most of my clients are drawn to a fun, flirty nature in a woman. The problem is, most women do not often feel fun and flirty.', 66734, 0), (489603, 'If I went to them all dressed up and flashed a nice smile for the cameras it would probably be easier for me to get work. But I just can''t tolerate it.', 66790, 0), (489604, 'I''m always trying to make myself laugh. I''m the most enthusiastic audience I''m likely to find, so if it doesn''t make me smile then it probably won''t work on you. The jokes that only make me shrug get cut.', 28809, 0), (489605, 'You can always tell folks from nonfolks. Folks like to feel good, like to smile for the camera when there''s a big photo opportunity for a really good cause.', 9597, 0), (489606, 'I wish I was told to look after my teeth when I was younger. My smile is really important to me and one of my biggest assets, so I''m very conscious that I need to keep it in top condition.', 73212, 0), (489607, 'I''m a fun song maker. I love to make people smile. I also love to see them big, burly dudes crying because their wives'' song is ''Die a Happy Man.''', 22972, 0), (489608, 'I think one of my first jokes - in the black community, there''s people who have jokes about skin tone. People like, ''You so black, you purple.'' ''You so black, you gotta smile so we can see you at night.''', 69726, 0), (489609, 'Crowds are the most difficult thing for me these days because I have to walk with my head down and my eyes averted. There''s still that part of me that wants to hold my head up, make eye contact and smile.', 45842, 0), (489610, 'I suffered from post-natal depression after Rowan was born. I had a healthy, beautiful baby girl and I couldn''t look at her. I couldn''t hold her, smile at her. All I wanted was to disappear and die.', 65022, 0), (489611, 'Country music in the mid-''90s was a big influence on my career, and I played all the songs that are referenced in ''94'' back in my club days. Joe Diffie was rocking a sick mullet, and he was hotter than ever... just putting out monster hit after monster hit. It totally takes me back to those days, and it makes me smile every time I hear it.', 22996, 0), (489612, 'When you have to work, work with a smile.', 69652, 0), (489613, 'I like to post positive content, and I like to try and make people smile. That''s why those videos are popular. I don''t fake it.', 70063, 0), (489614, 'Ostensibly rigorous and realistic, contemporary conservatism is an ideology of denial. Its symbol is a smile button.', 52664, 0), (489615, 'I bring people on stage with me. It''s a good time, and people love to join in on the party. Show me a smile, and I''ll show you one back.', 69363, 0), (489616, 'After six years without seeing one, I love just seeing a smile - every smile I see gives me hope.', 7906, 0), (489617, 'It''s a blessing because the Baldwin vibe on the street is what I live for the most. I think our name is something that a lot of people get a good feeling about and brings a smile to their face, and we''re very fortunate.', 69364, 0), (489618, 'Bob Dylan has always sealed his decisions with the unexplainable. His motives for withholding the release of the magnificent ''Basement Tapes'' will be as forever obscure as Brian Wilson''s reasons for the destruction of the tapes for ''Smile.''', 70699, 0), (489619, 'I have always loved a hard-faced girl. I get that Alison Goldfrapp isn''t easy, and I like her belligerence. She''s deeply sexy and controlled, like a Strict Machine, and it seems to wind the b''jesus out of the women I know. On the outside, I watch and smile and will her on like a twisted silent maiden aunt in the dark corner.', 70700, 0), (489620, 'I had ordered long legs, but they never arrived. My eyes are weird too, one is gray and the other is green. I have a crooked smile and my nose looks like a ski slope. No, I would not win a Miss contest.', 64133, 0), (489621, 'I have had wrinkles on my forehead and my smile line since I was a kid. I see them in my own kids. I know what they''re going to look like. So it''s kind of like that''s my personality. I feel the older you get, too, the more confident you become just in your own skin.', 70235, 0), (489622, 'I just want to show the fans my big smile and play the game that I love.', 66879, 0), (489623, 'Anyone who''s ever driven to Atlantic City knows that Trump''s got a big billboard. For years, you used to see his angry face on it. I said, ''Trump, that expression is making people afraid to go to the Taj Mahal. Why don''t you give them a big smile.? ''C''mon in, folks! Spend your money here!'' I think we got that corrected.', 66610, 0), (489624, 'Red carpets seem so glamorous, but you''re really just standing there sweating and worrying your hair is going to fall. And in the end, people are only going to see one picture of you. You just smile for one second and then you walk over to the side and check your phone. It''s pretty weird.', 69367, 0), (489625, 'Jessica Simpson is the youth ambassador for Operation Smile, and an episode of The Apprentice featured a team managing a charity concert she put on. Donald Trump came on stage and pledged a donation.', 36603, 0), (489626, 'I think Operation Smile is in more than 22 countries, mostly Third World. It just happened that my schedule opened up at the time they were heading to Vietnam.', 36603, 0), (489627, 'A smile costs about $240.', 36603, 0), (489628, 'In Delhi, where I grew up, commerce is brusque. You don''t ask each other how your day has been. You might not even smile. I''m not saying this is ideal - it''s how it is. You''re tied together by a transaction. The customer doesn''t tremble before complaining about how cold his food is.', 15932, 0), (489629, 'If I am not mistaken, it was a British poet who said that ''no one is properly dressed unless he wears a smile.''', 2014, 0), (489630, 'I''ve never liked my smile, you see. I should have had braces as a kid, but I was too proud and too vain. And I didn''t want to be bullied at school.', 72719, 0), (489631, 'I''m a huge sun baby. As soon as the sun comes out, my smile gets bigger, so I''m constantly smiling in L.A. It''s a fantastic place to be.', 72719, 0), (489632, 'People need to understand that the Lauryn Hill they were exposed to in the beginning was all that was allowed in that arena at the time. I had to step away for the sake of the machine. I was being way too compromised. I felt uncomfortable having to smile in someone''s face when I really didn''t like them or know them well enough to like.', 2021, 0), (489633, 'It''s very strange to go to cities like London and New York. People walk so quickly, they seem to be in a hurry all the time. And you don''t say ''Hi'' to everyone you meet, and you don''t smile to everyone you meet, because there''s just so many. Which is also very strange.', 70273, 0), (489634, 'Genuine expressions of emotion rarely persist longer than five seconds and almost never longer than 10. A fixed smile is likely to conceal anger, anxiety, or some other negative emotion.', 73298, 0), (489635, 'Watching movies in the U.S. is great fun because they get every joke, they smile, they laugh so much; it''s a great feeling.', 3939, 0), (489636, 'I was so embarrassed about mispronouncing words. I just knew how to smile.', 66881, 0), (489637, 'He taught me never to smile, which helps me when I visit disaster sites.', 47639, 0), (489638, 'And I like the look on people''s faces when I say I''m doing this movie called Pride and Prejudice and they kind of smile, and then I say I''m in a movie called Doom and they kind of do a double take and try and put the two things together. And they never quite manage to.', 72920, 0), (489639, 'Smile, it''s better than a poke in the eye.', 67402, 0), (489640, '''Halal in the Family'' will expose a broad audience to some of the realities of being Muslim in America. By using satire, we will encourage people to reconsider their assumptions about Muslims, while providing a balm to those experiencing anti-Muslim bias. I also hope those Uncles and Aunties out there will crack a smile!', 68672, 0), (489641, 'I''d much rather have sat there and just been a fly on the wall, instead of having to smile at people. I''d rather have been a waitress. Just gone round and stared at people.', 51822, 0), (489642, 'Many people say I smile more in Africa than in Sweden.', 3753, 0), (489643, 'If I buy a Fiat Uno, I''ll read that, for a man like me, a Ferrari was more suitable. If instead I buy a Ferrari, they''ll write that I should have kept my feet on the ground and bought a Fiat. If I smile, I''m not serious. If I don''t smile, I''m a rich sulker that doesn''t enjoy having the most beautiful job in the world.', 73451, 0), (489644, 'I have my father''s lopsided mouth. When I smile, my lips slope to one side. My doctor sister calls it my cerebral palsy mouth. I am very much a daddy''s girl, and even though I would rather my smile wasn''t crooked, there is something moving for me about having a mouth exactly like my father''s.', 2133, 0), (489645, 'It is clear I was never the Pretty Girl. I had my two front teeth knocked out when I was 10 and didn''t fix them until I was 19. I have a crooked smile and a nose that looks like it''s been broken 12 times but never has been. My nose was always red, so people called me Rudolph. My whole face is off-center.', 67842, 0), (489646, 'When it''s your will versus another person''s will, the worst thing you can do is smile in their face when you''re competing. That''s what I tell our guys. Go have fun.', 75333, 0), (489647, 'I''m one of those guys that - as far as relationships and stuff go - if you smile at me, I''m like, ''Let''s date for three years'' - which is just ridiculous.', 69291, 0), (489648, 'It brings a smile to my face every time I look in the record book and see my name with the likes of Hutson and Lance Alworth and Raymond Berry, some of the fabled receivers of the NFL. It''s all like a dream to me. I can''t believe it''s true.', 67826, 0), (489649, 'I know virtually no one of my age who can remember a hug, or a smile from their father, or a ''Let''s go play football.''', 71430, 0), (489650, 'What I always think about when I think about ''Girls'' is Lena being in a scene where she''s very vulnerable, possibly directing, acting, and she''s probably written the dialogue. It''s 2 in the morning. Everyone''s tired. Everyone''s grumpy. And she has a smile on her face and kindness for everyone who interacts with her.', 73917, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489651, 'I''m a car fanatic and each morning I wake up with a smile on my face, whether I''m commentating on the Formula One or at Silver Hatch racetrack in Roary the Racing Car.', 75587, 0), (489652, 'I kept hiding my smile in pictures throughout middle school and most of high school until picture day came my senior year.', 68755, 0), (489653, 'When I was little, I didn''t smile much. Don''t get me wrong. I was a happy kid, but I couldn''t stand the space, dead center, in between my teeth. Yeah, I could whistle through it, but so what? That didn''t win me many points on the playground in Medfield, Massachusetts.', 68755, 0), (489654, 'When you''re watching somebody read your material and they smile and nod, you know you''ve found that place where your experience and their experience match, even though they aren''t the same exact experience.', 3265, 0), (489655, 'I just sing the stuff that makes me smile, makes me feel like I didn''t sell myself out.', 66236, 0), (489656, 'I think people take a liking to a voice or something that makes them smile and feel good about themselves.', 70734, 0), (489657, 'You have to tell guys to ask you on a date. Smile when you do it - however that works, I''m not ''Cosmo.'' But yeah - not a lot of people know how to ''court'' anymore, sorry.', 26918, 0), (489658, 'I''m happy to help Crest Whitestrips on their mission to inspire photographers everywhere to capture smile moments and would encourage aspiring photographers to express themselves through their photos.', 74184, 0), (489659, 'As soon as you ''Botox'' your smile lines away, you lose part of your identity.', 74184, 0), (489660, 'Americans think Soviets are so grim. I want them to see that they can smile.', 65730, 0), (489661, '''Unbreakable Smile'' was based off one of the songs I wrote for the album - it was actually the first song I wrote for the album without realizing it yet. I think I wanted to name the album that because it seemed like that was just the theme of that chapter in my life and just the theme of all the songs put together.', 75692, 0), (489662, 'My grandmother, whom we call Biel, thinks it''s very unbecoming of me not to smile for the paparazzi. So every time I see them, I think, ''Smile for Biel!''', 69216, 0), (489663, 'In the car on my way to premieres and awards shows, I''ll sit with tissue paper under my armpits so I don''t soil the delicate dress fabric. The whole time, I''m telling myself, ''Please don''t sweat, please don''t sweat.'' I throw the tissues out right before I step out of the car, and nobody ever knows! I just put on a smile and fake it.', 69216, 0), (489664, 'For me, I think the Lord wanted me to win to put a smile on Chinese people''s faces.', 67123, 0), (489665, 'I want to put concepts in front of people that make them laugh or smile or even hate what I do. I''m not interested in just putting clothes in stores.', 68520, 0), (489666, 'When checking in at an airport, no matter how rude the check-in person is to you, always smile and be nice because you don''t know what kind of day they''ve had. You are going on holiday and they''re stuck wherever they are. Be nice to them because they can re-route your baggage to wherever they feel like.', 75693, 0), (489667, 'I travel around the world, experiencing every language, every religion... some places where there''s just no reason to smile, because their lives are so difficult.', 70737, 0), (489668, 'The same people who smile in my face would be the same ones to talk behind my back.', 75694, 0), (489669, 'I tend to look out for things with a resonance to my youth - artists or objects that seemed romantic all those years ago. I never buy anything purely for its value. I like possessions that smile back at me.', 74736, 0), (489670, 'The biggest thing we get out of it is seeing the kids smile. And hopefully we will also see that the lessons we''re teaching - not only the fundamentals of hockey, but also the life values - are sinking in.', 11181, 0), (489671, 'I enjoy the process of composing music. The first time I hear a song, it has to bring a smile to my lips. You have to tap your feet and be able to sing the song.', 39410, 0), (489672, 'The smile on your face lets me know that you need me, there''s a truth in your heart that says you''ll never leave me, and the touch of your hand says you''ll catch me whenever I fall.', 71757, 0), (489673, 'I love a girl that can make me laugh. I am not really a laugh-at-things type of guy and I don''t smile and laugh all the time... But if a girl can make me laugh... I''m in love!!!!', 69774, 0), (489674, 'It''s lovely to work with a group of actors who make you laugh and smile.', 75695, 0), (489675, 'I was doing a Broadway musical called ''Smile'' with Howard Ashman and Marvin Hamlisch in 1984/5 when it abruptly closed. Howard was in the middle of pre-production for ''The Little Mermaid,'' so he kindly invited all the girls in our cast to audition for the film.', 69157, 0), (489676, 'The Viennese wash everything. Where else in the world does the government hire public servants to wash public telephone booths and the glass over traffic lights? Every time I see someone doing these things, I smile like a child.', 11225, 0), (489677, 'I love the Rio Grande Valley. I always say it''s home - Texas is home. I''ve been out in L.A. a little over ten years, and I still get so excited when I go back home. It just feels comfortable; it makes me smile.', 75208, 0), (489678, 'I''m so glad cities have personalities, just like people have personalities. That''s something that makes me smile.', 75335, 0), (489679, 'I get very nervous whenever I think about it. I''ve never done a serious play, and I have such awe of the woman - she''s really my only idol. It''s going to be a big stretch - certain people come out on stage and your face muscles automatically tense and you get ready to smile.', 75144, 0), (489680, 'But I am convinced that those Jews who stand aside today with a malicious smile and with their hands in their trousers'' pockets will also want to dwell in our beautiful home.', 17762, 0), (489681, 'Bjorn was a different breed, I threw my best material at him, but he would never smile, but that added to the charm when he played me and Mac. We were going nuts and losing our mind and he was sitting back like he was on a Sunday stroll.', 60464, 0), (489682, 'On street corners everywhere, people are looking at their cell phones, and it''s easy to dismiss this as some sort of bad trend in human culture. But the truth is life is being lived there. When they smile - right, you''ve seen people stop - all of a sudden, life is being lived there, somewhere up in that weird, dense network.', 54900, 0), (489683, 'I like girls that have a nice smile and nice eyes. I want to date a girl who understands my busy schedule and that I have to be on tour a lot. And she has to make me laugh!', 22967, 0), (489684, 'I was kind of like the Rhea Perlman of the bar. I was like Carla on ''Cheers.'' People were more afraid of me. There was a point where I got a little surly. There were only so many chicken wings I could serve before losing the smile on my face.', 71101, 0), (489685, 'I watched Gene Kelly for his smile, for his energy. Vittorio Gassman for his movement. Clark Gable for his mustache. And I watched Lassie who was happy as a dog.', 72258, 0), (489686, 'Some people would rather have a lie that makes them smile than a truth that makes them cry. I''m the opposite I''d rather have people make me cry with the truth than try to make me smile. ', 69028, 0), (489687, 'Being in a rock band is about touring. It''s about writing songs and it''s about making records but it''s also about taking a wonderful smile onto that stage and making the people feel good about themselves.', 75696, 0), (489688, 'We need prisons because there are some hardcore criminals, but I never met a guy who has been in jail that came out with a smile on his face thinking, ''Right, that''s it - now I am going to be good!''', 75697, 0), (489689, 'I think the divine is like a huge smile that breaks somewhere in the sea within you, and gradually comes up again.', 400, 0), (489690, 'We''re teaching our kids that attributes as vague and relatively meaningless as a toothy smile or a fine head of hair make a fine statement about a person.', 75221, 0), (489691, 'We have such a long, familiar history with Peter Falk. The minute his mug is on that screen people smile.', 12009, 0), (489692, 'Women do come up to me, and they tell me what they think! I''ve gotten great compliments on my eyes and my smile. But I don''t see myself as sexy.', 67923, 0), (489693, 'My mum is great for keeping hold of old classics - pieces of clothing that never age and never go out of fashion. She also says, ''Make sure you always smile - it makes everything look better!''', 70327, 0), (489694, 'We tried to set up a company that patterned ourselves after Southwest in all the fun, the spirit, the great people, the smile, the efficiency side of it, but we''ve added some extras that people aren''t used to finding on Southwest.', 75698, 0), (489695, 'When I see these young girls who are dreaming the dream that I''m living, it''s very very exciting and it puts a big smile on my face.', 66974, 0), (489696, 'I love Motown, that whole era. Marvin Gaye, Smokey Robinson. I just put on Pandora, and put it on Motown, and it makes me smile; makes me smile so much.', 68122, 0), (489697, 'I think ultimately I make people happy: Whether I''m doing the stage show, giving somebody a makeover, or designing clothing, the end goal is to make people smile.', 3675, 0), (489698, 'People smile at me as if they know me. I just smile back. They probably might know me.', 75699, 0), (489699, 'I don''t want my writing to be work to read. My main goal is completely shameless entertainment. I want people to smile and giggle and enjoy the book. I''m not trying to save the world through literature.', 2342, 0), (489700, 'I can retire from football with a smile on my face.', 75700, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489701, 'We forget that this music, music made by my brothers and sisters, is still a baby. It''s just beginning. When I think of the possibilities, it makes me smile.', 71751, 0), (489702, 'When you see that many people with a smile on their face, then you must be doing something right.', 69787, 0), (489703, 'A game one of my sisters will play with me in my first year of being alive is called Good Baby, Bad Baby. This consists of being told I am a good baby until I smile and laugh, then being told I am a bad baby until I burst into tears. This training will stand me in good stead all through my life.', 8022, 0), (489704, 'I can sing and dance. I can smile - a lot.', 1738, 0), (489705, 'I smile so much at the theater my face hurts when I leave.', 75701, 0), (489706, 'Southerners smile more than other Americans.', 72674, 0), (489707, 'In case you haven''t heard, my girlfriends and I have declared the summer of 2012 as the best summer ever. The best way to document said ''best summer ever'' is with a good ol'' disposable camera. Smile, click, move on! Nobody gets pic approval, and there''s no time wasted gathering around the camera to analyze a moment that just happened.', 74305, 0), (489708, 'I have found that a smile and a stick will carry you through all right, and in ninety-nine cases out of a hundred it is the smile that does the trick.', 68607, 0), (489709, 'I once called a guy into his own office and spun around in his own chair to greet him. That kind of thing may be why I quit, before I got into serious trouble. I would smile and the person would get so upset. But you do a thousand of those things, and it makes you weird.', 75702, 0), (489710, 'My father was short for a man, with a child''s plaything for a name - Spinner. He had flawless dark brown skin and a head full of big, wet-looking curls, black as oil. And he had the smile of a scoundrel - the kind of smile that disarmed men and undressed women.', 7234, 0), (489711, 'The person that''s always talkin'', you don''t have to worry about that person. The person that while you''re in his face, he''s just lookin'' at you with a smile on his face, that''s the guy you worry about.', 66914, 0), (489712, 'The Parthenon without the marbles is like a smile with a tooth missing.', 73866, 0), (489713, 'What do I like in a girl? I like a girl that likes me, a girl that knows how to smile and see the bright side of things. A girl that makes me a better person.', 67511, 0), (489714, 'Both of our children are adopted, and my wife and I didn''t go out of ways to find kids that looked like us. We were just happy to have some kids. And people tell me all the time that they look like us, and that''s because they learn to smile and laugh and move their head a certain way from studying their parents'' faces.', 68612, 0), (489715, 'While you''re improvising, you may come up with something which will break him up. As soon as that smile comes out, you know that, hey, we''re having fun.', 68617, 0), (489716, 'I love a good laugh as well, I think that''s so important in life, which is probably why I''ve dabbled in comedy writing as well as horror. I think if you can make someone laugh or smile it''s the most special thing in the world.', 71338, 0), (489717, 'When I was younger, I''d go to the Museum of Television and Radio in New York and watch this beautiful clip of Billie Holiday playing with a bassist, a pianist and Gerry Mulligan, who was a friend of mine, on baritone sax. At one point, she looks over at Gerry, and they just smile. When those moments happen, it''s just lovely.', 73616, 0), (489718, 'I don''t really remember a time younger than 5 years old that I didn''t have skates on because all I can remember is every day, tying up my skates and a big smile on my face, excited to go on the ice.', 1529, 0), (489719, 'When trying to remember my share in the glow of the eternal present, in the smile of God, I return to my childhood, too, for that is where the most significant discoveries turn up.', 45464, 0), (489720, 'Oh, I talk about things; I drive my husband insane. And I can''t tell a lie. Everyone knows. I do this smile thing.', 413, 0), (489721, 'I come to work with a smile and I leave with a laugh, and I''m so grateful.', 75703, 0), (489722, 'I wasn''t as used to the new dumb questions, so when men I had once thought of as wise daddies now asked me ''How do you write?'' I did not try and spill red wine in their suede pants. I would just smile and say, ''On a typewriter in the mornings when there''s nothing else to do.''', 27779, 0), (489723, 'I don''t have to jump up and smile just because TV wants me to.', 2100, 0), (489724, 'I love to see the smiles on people''s faces when you cook for them. I love to go to different restaurants. I want to cook because I know this acting isn''t going to last forever, and I want something to fall back on. It''s another way to make people smile.', 15485, 0), (489725, 'People often expect me to be very serious, but it''s not like my record company told me not to smile in photographs, because I was like that anyway.', 75704, 0), (489726, 'I''ve covered a lot of ground geographically and emotionally and for years I lost my connection with my family. But the best comfort you can have, whether you are on the phone or sitting there in the living room with them, is with your parents, and to me family has always meant protection. When you smile you get a smile back, unconditionally.', 72257, 0), (489727, 'Jeff Kinney is tall and has a great smile, but don''t be fooled, he''s as slick as they come. A real player. And how he came up with a book that appeals to kids ages 8-13 baffles me. He''s an unbelievably kind man with a great family.', 75705, 0), (489728, 'I have my own dance and production companies, and acting is my creative outlet. It''s what I''m passionate about. I''ve actually created a lifestyle where I could act for free. I could get a job to pay the bills and act on the weekends to make me smile.', 75706, 0), (489729, 'Very few things are totally devoid of any possibility of humor. If you are aware of that possibility and alive to the scene becoming that way, then it just happens naturally. That''s what I feel living is like, too. I find a lot of things that make me smile or make me laugh over the course of the day.', 54765, 0), (489730, 'In my whole career, I''ve never seen this type of race that you had to wait for the last day. There''s so many teams that are involved. You''ve got to smile because we''re in it.', 67352, 0), (489731, 'I have a smile 24/7.', 75707, 0), (489732, 'My sculptures cause an uproar, astonishment, and put a smile on your face.', 69906, 0), (489733, 'Remember that it is not enough to abstain from lying by word of mouth; for the worst lies are often conveyed by a false look, smile, or act.', 68322, 0), (489734, 'Anybody who knows me knows that I''m just here to put a smile on people''s faces.', 74469, 0), (489735, 'There is no point to samba if it doesn''t make you smile.', 72734, 0), (489736, 'We never respect those who amuse us, however we may smile at their comic powers.', 71952, 0), (489737, 'I do love to walk around in New York because people will notice me, smile, but they never bother anyone. New Yorkers are very cool. I love New York.', 75708, 0), (489738, 'I think the deafness affects me more than I realise; I think it makes me more tired. I loathe parties. I attend, smile and leave.', 73184, 0), (489739, 'Growing up, I was a huge fan of horror movies. There''s nothing more fun than going into a movie with a smile because you know you''re going to be scared to death. There''s something thrilling about sitting there waiting for a scare to happen.', 75709, 0), (489740, 'All of the narration in ''Smile'' is first-person. Most of the books that I grew up reading had first-person narrators for some reason. My diaries were written in this voice, and since this story is autobiographical, it just felt like a natural extension.', 69254, 0), (489741, 'I smile every time I hear that I''m a fan favorite or a teenage hottie. It is a nice compliment, and the remarks from the fans are great.', 73992, 0), (489742, 'I like guys with a nice smile. I know it''s cliche, but it''s so true! I like a guy with a nice smile and nice eyes.', 70655, 0), (489743, 'One of the most obvious parts of my character is the smile, and if I wasn''t comfortable in myself then I wouldn''t be able to smile so much.', 72414, 0), (489744, 'When most people think of Woodrow Wilson, they see a dour minister''s son who never cracked a smile, where in fact he was a man of genuine joy and great sadness.', 11787, 0), (489745, 'As long as I am still interested and curious, I enjoy getting up in the morning, but I can''t say I have a happy smile on my face 24/7.', 75710, 0), (489746, 'My favorite books are the ones that make me smile for hours after reading them. I want that for my readers, for the sweetness to linger. Sort of like chocolate, but without the calories.', 637, 0), (489747, 'Football has to work really hard to put a smile on people''s face and not to be so focused on the question of money. Everything is in danger of losing its soul if you''re always going to sell out to the highest bidder.', 75711, 0), (489748, 'Tanzanians are some of the friendliest you''ll ever meet, insisting on a welcoming smile and wave as they pass you on the streets, exclaiming ''Jambo!''', 75712, 0), (489749, 'I like outgoing girls with a lovely smile and beautiful eyes.', 69243, 0), (489750, 'I hope there have been times when I made you all proud, or made you all smile or at least piqued your interest in this wonderful institution we call government.', 72568, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489751, 'One study found that people who smile in childhood photographs are less likely to get a divorce.', 73834, 0), (489752, 'I collect all the reviews of the films I turned down. And when they''re bad - I have to smile.', 22263, 0), (489753, 'I can''t wait for summer in the city! I love all the free activities in the parks that become available to us New Yorkers. Yoga and movie screenings in Bryant Park, concerts in Central Park - there''s so much more available to the New York community in the summer! And everyone just seems to smile more.', 69200, 0), (489754, 'I enjoy what Twitter is because I can really connect with the fans and it''s a great way to share information with them and it''s also a great way to entertain. I like being able to put a smile on people''s faces and letting them know what I''m doing.', 75713, 0), (489755, 'If you''re going to kill someone there isn''t much reason to get all worked up about it and angry - you just pull the trigger. Angry discussions beforehand are a waste of time. We need to smile at Novell while we pull the trigger.', 75714, 0), (489756, 'I''m not looking for anything more than any other guy. I like a good smile. Pretty eyes. She has to be active, like not play-sports active, but she''ll play air hockey, do some pool, go for rides on the Santa Monica Pier. I would much rather have fun with her than do the cool thing.', 75715, 0), (489757, 'I''m the middle man. I try to keep people happy. I go out of my way to get a smile. That''s the way my mother raised me.', 75683, 0), (489758, 'When you''re surrounded by feathers and sequins and ridiculous Lycra outfits, it''s impossible not to have a smile on your face.', 20400, 0), (489759, 'It''s been a hard time to celebrate, to come out with a smile. But I''m an American. Naomi asked me to come out to support other Americans, and here I am.', 75716, 0), (489760, 'You see some of these actors, they have a permanent smile on their face. How can they do that? It really fascinates me.', 74586, 0), (489761, 'Indeed it is possible to stand with one foot on the inevitable ''banana peel'' of life with both eyes peering into the Great Beyond, and still be happy, comfortable, and serene - if we will even so much as smile.', 71947, 0), (489762, 'I don''t smile much, and I never laugh. If you''d been through what I''ve been through, you wouldn''t be smiling, either.', 75717, 0), (489763, 'I love to see people laugh and put a smile on peoples'' faces. Anytime I''m doing that I''m happy.', 75718, 0), (489764, 'I just smile. And they - my opponents don''t like it when I smile at them. They think I''m playing or something. But - like I smile throughout the whole fight. Sometimes I''ll be throwing combinations and I just smile and stick my tongue out at them.', 75719, 0), (489765, 'Whenever I run into prejudice. I smile and feel sorry for them, and I say to myself, There''s one more argument for birth control.', 75720, 0), (489766, 'I don''t remember ever deciding to become a performer. I just always was. I began performing by mimicking the performers on the new television that first took the attention away from me as the baby of the household. I continued performing to put a smile on my grandmother''s face and always considered her when accepting or declining roles.', 75721, 0), (489767, 'When I first came to America, you know, I would look at the newsstands and see the women on the magazine covers. I had never seen anyone smile the way these girls smile! It''s like they have nothing to worry about!', 20831, 0), (489768, '''Try Again'' - every time I hear that song, it just brings a smile to your face. When you''re feeling like crap, and you hear, ''Dust yourself off and try again,'' it kind of just puts you in a different mindset, 100 percent.', 75722, 0), (489769, 'When I draw my caricature self-portrait, I always do a huge smile.', 73343, 0), (489770, 'His smile is like the silver plate on a coffin.', 16691, 0), (489771, 'If you meet a woman in a burqa, she can''t reply to your smile. It''s a denial of identity.', 74818, 0), (489772, 'I was brought up by my father to think that the best thing in life was to be charming, to have a nice smile, always to be liked.', 75723, 0), (489773, 'Seeing Michelle Obama''s bright color choices, and how she made people smile and reinforced Obama''s platforms of hope and change, was inspiring.', 31858, 0), (489774, 'I figured out, I guess, that the job just makes me happy if it''s not number one. So if it all works, great. If it doesn''t, I still go home, look at my kids, and I have a big smile on my face.', 75724, 0), (489775, 'They gave each other a smile with a future in it.', 9627, 0), (489776, 'I am a joyful conservative, unafraid to articulate big ideas with an optimistic smile.', 75725, 0), (489777, 'As happy a man as any in the world, for the whole world seems to smile upon me!', 22310, 0), (489778, 'Ever since I was 2 or 3, I loved to perform for people. I would walk up to another table in a restaurant and crack a joke, sing a song, do a dance, or something entertaining, and the ''audience'' would almost always smile and laugh.', 75726, 0), (489779, 'Whenever I look at a baby or children in general, I smile and just want to play with them.', 75727, 0), (489780, 'I play guys who never smile, and I never stop smiling.', 75109, 0), (489781, 'My mom''s one of the toughest ladies I know. I''ve seen her lose both her brothers, both her parents. She''s been through a lot, and to see her get up every day and put a smile on her face, that shows nothing but strength.', 70516, 0), (489782, 'No one is so completely disenchanted with the world, or knows it so thoroughly, or is so utterly disgusted with it, that when it begins to smile upon him he does not become partially reconciled to it.', 7895, 0), (489783, 'I sat in at every club in New York City, jamming with musicians, because it felt right - and because it felt right and we were having fun - the people dancing and sipping their drinks in the clubs felt it too and it made them smile.', 75728, 0), (489784, 'When life takes me on a new journey, I simply remember the smile my first ballet recital put on my face and I move forward.', 74837, 0), (489785, 'And History will smile to think that this is the species for which Socrates and Jesus Christ died.', 75729, 0), (489786, 'I try to make people smile and dance, not think about things or educate them.', 75730, 0), (489787, 'The essence of life is the smile of round female bottoms, under the shadow of cosmic boredom.', 1559, 0), (489788, 'The weaker the country, the stronger the smile.', 75648, 0), (489789, 'From a very young age, music was very much in my house. I would sit with my mom, with the old LPs, listening to The Beatles and Carly Simon and Lionel Richie. The old LPs used to have the lyrics. From there, I would put on dance and music displays for my family, just to entertain them and make people laugh and smile.', 75731, 0), (489790, 'When I used to wrestle professionally, I preferred being the bad guy known as ''The Heel;'' you would get to ''work the crowd,'' getting them to hate you and want to see you lose, while the good guy ''Babyface'' would walk in, smile and shake hands with a few kids, and his acting job was done.', 75732, 0), (489791, 'I spend days on my Xperia logging on Facebook chatting with my friends and family at home; I love listening to Rihanna and Pink and watching movies. Basically, anything that makes me smile, but most of my fans will know that I am always smiling!', 75733, 0), (489792, 'My eyes are different sizes, my nose is too broad at the bridge and squishes up when I laugh, and my lips are sorta funny when I smile.', 75734, 0), (489793, 'I love to smile.', 75735, 0), (489794, 'Arnold Palmer has what I call an ''Eisenhower smile''. Those two men, they''d smile and their whole faces would look so pleasant; it was like they were smiling all over.', 73019, 0), (489795, 'When my time ends, I want people to say, ''Man her music made me smile; it just enlightened my life; it inspired me; it made me feel good every time.''', 75736, 0), (489796, 'I don''t hear a lot about elected officials that are men talking about whether they smile a lot. My dad was in elected office my entire life. I don''t remember many smiles, and nobody commented about it. He was serious about his job, and so am I.', 74239, 0), (489797, 'After God and my family, it''s surf. I don''t imagine me not surfing. Surf brings me smile every day.', 72206, 0), (489798, 'I grew up in a household without a TV. We lived next door to a library for a while, and at one point, I checked out all the books in the fairy tale section. I remember the librarian''s quiet smile as I''d bring back one stack and exchange it for another.', 7839, 0), (489799, 'Tell me not of joy: there''s none Now my little sparrow''s gone; He, just as you, Would toy and woo, He would chirp and flatter me, He would hang the wing awhile, Till at length he saw me smile, Lord! how sullen he would be!', 75737, 0), (489800, 'You keep shooting. You hope it goes in, and you smile.', 75738, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489801, 'We''re under some gross misconception that we''re a good species, going somewhere important, and that at the last minute we''ll correct our errors and God will smile on us. It''s delusion.', 16002, 0), (489802, 'Someone asked me the other day what it feels like to see all my ''old stuff'' reappearing, at long last, in digital. And I had to smile because to me it doesn''t feel like ''old stuff.''', 10542, 0), (489803, 'Oh, the ignorance of us upon whom Providence did not sufficiently smile to permit us to be born in New England.', 75739, 0), (489804, 'In masks outrageous and austere, The years go by in single file; But none has merited my fear, And none has quite escaped my smile.', 31101, 0), (489805, 'When you consider all the stars I have managed, mere submarines make me smile.', 63209, 0), (489806, 'When Fortune smiles, I smile to think how quickly she will frown.', 4440, 0), (489807, 'Action is drama. If we cannot make the audience laugh, smile or cry with us, we are not actors.', 75740, 0), (489808, 'I really get a smile that people think they have a right to even suggest how I give my money away. I have no mandate to give a dime to anybody.', 75741, 0), (489809, 'I always challenge myself. I get out in deep water and I always try to get back. But I get hung up. The audience never knows, but that''s when I smile the most, when I show the most ivory.', 75742, 0), (489810, 'I will know how to hold you just by the look in your eye, I will never forget - not even on the day that I die. This is a promise of my passion for you, smile at me and make it true.', 75743, 0), (489811, 'We think of stars as celestial beings. And once in a while, they smile at us from the pages of ''People'' magazine.', 75744, 0), (489812, 'In junior high school, I was an object of pure ridicule for my dress, withdrawal, and asocial manner. Dozens of times, I saw individuals laugh and smile more in ten to fifteen minutes than I did in all my life up to then.', 75745, 0), (489813, 'A beautiful woman delights the eye; a wise woman, the understanding; a pure one, the soul.', 62388, 0), (489814, 'A tramp, a gentleman, a poet, a dreamer, a lonely fellow, always hopeful of romance and adventure.', 454, 0), (489815, 'When you look at me, when you think of me, I am in paradise.', 1711, 0), (489816, 'Kiss me and you will see how important I am.', 140, 0), (489817, 'There''s something about the sound of a train that''s very romantic and nostalgic and hopeful.', 1017, 0), (489818, 'We are each of us angels with only one wing, and we can only fly by embracing one another.', 71280, 0), (489819, 'Heard melodies are sweet, but those unheard are sweeter.', 191, 0), (489820, 'Tradition wears a snowy beard, romance is always young.', 997, 0), (489821, 'All the beautiful sentiments in the world weigh less than a single lovely action.', 1247, 0), (489822, 'Bid me to love, and I will give a loving heart to thee.', 8674, 0), (489823, 'There is no instinct like that of the heart.', 62558, 0), (489824, 'All the windows of my heart I open to the day.', 997, 0), (489825, 'When I walk with you I feel as if I had a flower in my buttonhole.', 1711, 0), (489826, 'How far away the stars seem, and how far is our first kiss, and ah, how old my heart.', 62867, 0), (489827, 'Today I begin to understand what love must be, if it exists... When we are parted, we each feel the lack of the other half of ourselves. We are incomplete like a book in two volumes of which the first has been lost. That is what I imagine love to be: incompleteness in absence.', 10465, 0), (489828, 'A man''s kiss is his signature.', 978, 0), (489829, 'A realist, in Venice, would become a romantic by mere faithfulness to what he saw before him.', 10610, 0), (489830, 'I have often been downcast but never in despair; I regard our hiding as a dangerous adventure, romantic and interesting at the same time. In my diary, I treat all the privations as amusing.', 986, 0), (489831, 'Romance is tempestuous. Love is calm.', 12469, 0), (489832, 'When I give I give myself.', 1127, 0), (489833, 'I''m a hopeless romantic and I believe that you can find love in many different places and be very conflicted. I''ve discovered as I''ve grown up that life is far more complicated than you think it is when you''re a kid. It isn''t just a straightforward fairytale.', 60126, 0), (489834, 'My heart is like a singing bird.', 600, 0), (489835, 'All I ever wanted was to be a sexy bride, and actually, I think I''ve turned into a romantic bride.', 69238, 0), (489836, 'Romantic love is an addiction.', 52746, 0), (489837, 'Be brave, young lovers, and follow your star.', 43349, 0), (489838, 'Breathless, we flung us on a windy hill, Laughed in the sun, and kissed the lovely grass.', 31057, 0), (489839, 'My personal decorating style is cozy, romantic and a little rustic, with a sense of whimsy.', 69555, 0), (489840, 'You feel very romantic when you''re in a ball gown. Everyone should wear one once in a while.', 71247, 0), (489841, 'When I was a kid, I knew the black and white version of ''Jane Eyre,'' and I guess I became interested in the idea of romantic love - of unrequited love and the tragedies of that; of what are the important things in life; what should one value over other materials.', 70058, 0), (489842, 'The most impactful place that I''ve been to where I was just completely awestruck, happy, moved is Victoria Falls between Zambia and Zimbabwe. It is probably the most beautiful and romantic place in the world.', 68255, 0), (489843, 'It is better to have loved and lost than never to have lost at all.', 4111, 0), (489844, 'I am a hopeless romantic. And I won''t stop till I get it right.', 69081, 0), (489845, 'It is really rare to find someone you really, really love and that you want to spend your life with and all that stuff that goes along with being married. I am one of those lucky people. And I think she feels that way too. So the romantic stuff is easy because you want them to be happy.', 68271, 0), (489846, 'I''m into all that sappy stuff - a surprise picnic, nice dinner, or traveling. I''m kind of an old romantic.', 75746, 0), (489847, 'Grunge is a hippied romantic version of punk.', 19768, 0), (489848, 'I''m a very loyal boyfriend. I''m a bit of a joker... I can be romantic, but not too sickly.', 12979, 0), (489849, 'I love the ukulele. It''s got a beautiful, melodic tone to it. There''s something innocent and romantic, and it''s just a grand instrument to play.', 67399, 0), (489850, 'I joined the air force. I took to it immediately when I arrived there. I did three years, eight months, and ten days in all, but it took me a year and a half to get disabused of my romantic notions about it.', 30247, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489851, 'I''m not religious, I''m not romantic and I live purely by logic. I make every decision by logic and sometimes that leads me to the right and sometimes to the wrong decision.', 25489, 0), (489852, 'I''m a teller of stories. I put bloody skins on my back and dance around the fire, and I say what the hunt was like. It''s not erudite; it''s not intellectual. I sail, run dogs, ride horses, play professional poker, and tell stories about the stuff I''ve been through. And I''m still a romantic; I still want Bambi to make it out of the fire.', 1392, 0), (489853, 'And I don''t believe that children are innocent. In fact, no one seriously believes that. Just go to a playground and watch the kids playing in the sandbox! The romantic notion of the sweet child is simply the parents projecting their own wishes.', 35830, 0), (489854, 'Romantic love can be terrifying. We experience another human being as enormously important to us. So there is surrender - not a surrender to the other person so much as to our feeling for the other person. What is the obstacle? The possibility of loss.', 6169, 0), (489855, 'French is the language that turns dirt into romance.', 578, 0), (489856, 'I think I meant that, given the circumstances of my childhood, I had the illusion that it''s easier to be alone. To have your relationships be casual and also to pose as a solitary person, because it was more romantic. You know, I was raised on the idea of the ramblin'' man and the loner.', 748, 0), (489857, 'Romantic love is painful.', 32686, 0), (489858, 'Love to me has meant different things at different junctures of my life. I''m not a hopeless romantic.', 68932, 0), (489859, 'I''ve always said that inside of me there is a rocker that wants to come out, but I''m a romantic rocker.', 68293, 0), (489860, 'What I''d really like to write is a romantic comedy. This is my favorite kind of movie. I feel almost embarrassed revealing this, because the genre has been so degraded in the past twenty years that saying you like romantic comedies is essentially an admission of mild stupidity.', 1289, 0), (489861, 'I do not like to work with patients who are in love. Perhaps it is because of envy - I, too, crave enchantment. Perhaps it is because love and psychotherapy are fundamentally incompatible. The good therapist fights darkness and seeks illumination, while romantic love is sustained by mystery and crumbles upon inspection.', 1196, 0), (489862, 'I am a romantic fool, no doubt about that.', 68537, 0), (489863, 'A boy is holding a girl so very tight in his arms tonight.', 74373, 0), (489864, 'Romantic love is mental illness. But it''s a pleasurable one. It''s a drug. It distorts reality, and that''s the point of it. It would be impossible to fall in love with someone that you really saw.', 1437, 0), (489865, 'Romance is everything.', 1267, 0), (489866, 'What is a kiss? Why this, as some approve: The sure, sweet cement, glue, and lime of love.', 8674, 0), (489867, 'There are certain romances that belong in certain cities, in a certain atmosphere, in a certain time.', 67573, 0), (489868, 'I''m very romantic. I''ve emptied flower shops.', 74746, 0), (489869, 'When the heart speaks, its language is the same under all latitudes.', 70829, 0), (489870, 'My dearly beloved if I am to die today and never see the sweet face of you I want you to know that I am no great man and am lucky to have such a woman as you.', 74323, 0), (489871, 'I''m a romantic, and we romantics are more sensitive to the way people feel. We love more, and we hurt more. When we''re hurt, we hurt for a long time.', 75720, 0), (489872, 'Is this not the true romantic feeling; not to desire to escape life, but to prevent life from escaping you.', 1971, 0), (489873, 'I think I''ll always be a hopeless romantic.', 34530, 0), (489874, 'I love to have my hair down I love to have my hair full... there''s something romantic about it. ', 38496, 0), (489875, 'I''m not romantic; I''m very practical. There are lots of fish in the sea; so whoever gets struck with your rod, one is as good as another.', 38710, 0), (489876, 'I saw Tequila Sunrise as a romantic picture with complex, bigger than life characters.', 68354, 0), (489877, 'Satan, really, is the romantic youth of Jesus re-appearing for a moment.', 265, 0), (489878, 'I''m better with my hands, and I always loved the slightly romantic idea of starting with bits of wood and being able to create something to sit on, to eat from, to store your clothes in.', 15479, 0), (489879, 'The idea of a soulmate is beautiful and very romantic to talk about it in a movie or a song, but in reality, I find it scary.', 69939, 0), (489880, 'If you''re a woman and a guy''s ever said anything romantic to you, he just left off the second part that would have made you sick if you could have heard it.', 536, 0), (489881, 'I am a hopeless romantic.', 67131, 0), (489882, 'Romantic music really stirs my soul. And, of course, I love Chinese music; it makes me feel closer to home.', 75747, 0), (489883, 'The gospel sets us free to become the romantic leaders of our marriages without fright or hesitation. Because we have been forever wooed by Jesus, we are now free to forever woo our wives.', 16728, 0), (489884, 'I''m a hopeless romantic. I love love. My middle name is Love. Valentine''s Day is my favorite holiday. I want to have a family and children. I am a sucker for every romantic comedy that comes out.', 2549, 0), (489885, 'I had a romantic, ''Aren''t I a good girl?'' take on divorce, but the truth is that was stupid.', 72617, 0), (489886, 'I will always be the hopeless romantic, more often pathetic than heroic.', 75748, 0), (489887, 'Being black, Latino, or Asian is not a genre. Romantic comedies, thrillers, action - those are genres. I think there''s a lot of people who want to have the conversation. I don''t think people are afraid of it, I just think it''s the time to have that conversation. Race is not a genre.', 73478, 0), (489888, 'Normally, things are viewed in these little segmented boxes. There''s classical, and then there''s jazz; romantic, and then there''s baroque. I find that very dissatisfying. I was trying to find the thread that connects one type of music - one type of musician - to another, and to follow that thread in some kind of natural, evolutionary way.', 3401, 0), (489889, 'New York was no mere city. It was instead an infinitely romantic notion, the mysterious nexus of all love and money and power, the shining and perishable dream itself.', 1170, 0), (489890, 'I once took the key off my girlfriend''s key ring so that I could surprise her when she got home. So I did this whole romantic setup in our bedroom with flowers and rose petals. She was so mad when she got home, but then when she walked in, she was so surprised.', 67132, 0), (489891, 'With ''Attachments,'' my goal was to write a really good romantic comedy. I wanted the reader to be smiling throughout.', 54, 0), (489892, 'I don''t think of death in a romantic way anymore.', 68214, 0), (489893, 'In terms of level of difficulty, it would go comedy, thriller, and then romantic drama.', 68229, 0), (489894, 'I''m always trying to reach a transcendent point, a romantic point, but reach it in a really unconventional way, a really profane way. To get to that romantic, touching, heartbreaking place, but through a lot of acts of profanity.', 30, 0), (489895, 'I am completely open to doing a romantic comedy, but I will never do something just for the sake of doing a specific genre or because it''s the time or place to do a different type of movie. I think that would be a huge mistake.', 68700, 0), (489896, 'Upsi is definitely the more romantic of the two. I am more laid back. We do have our differences of opinion sometimes. Upsi is always the first one to break the ice after an argument or a difference of opinion. That''s what I love most about her.', 67033, 0), (489897, 'If you look at romantic comedies as pieces of commerce, the audience is looking for wish fulfillment.', 13172, 0), (489898, 'I don''t understand why every guy is not a romantic. I enjoy it.', 69751, 0), (489899, 'I don''t get off on romantic parts. But I often think if I had had my dental work done early on, well, maybe.', 30247, 0), (489900, 'Fall 2013 was inspired by the 1970s equestrian lifestyle. I wanted to incorporate the moody and romantic - intricate baroque detailing and classic menswear elements - with something tougher and edgier in a nod to London''s rock n'' roll underground.', 71579, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489901, 'I love crying at romantic movies like ''The Notebook.'' I''m always bawling.', 55411, 0), (489902, 'The vampire was a complete change from the usual romantic characters I was playing, but it was a success.', 15789, 0), (489903, 'I am a die-hard romantic at heart and love the idea of love. But, when it comes to love, I kinda believe in the old world charm of romance - where there''s mystery and intrigue.', 69009, 0), (489904, 'Couples without kids have each other, their friends, families, and Siri to talk to. It''s not like they''re quarantining themselves in an underground bunker, never to take a romantic stroll on the beach or attend a Morrissey concert ever again. They''re just using birth control.', 49833, 0), (489905, 'I had written many things as a journalist, but I had no idea if I could write something scary or romantic or touching that wasn''t me writing about someone else''s life story. It was really exciting to try.', 68381, 0), (489906, 'Classical, Romantic, and Baroque music, that''s what I really like.', 75749, 0), (489907, 'Without romance, films will be boring. I doubt if people now understand romance, though they may claim it otherwise. I am very romantic in real life.', 74559, 0), (489908, 'I find it incredibly romantic that people should fight for a cause they believe in and be prepared to die for it.', 67626, 0), (489909, 'I''m not what you might call sexy, but I''m romantic. Let''s put it that way.', 1377, 0), (489910, 'The word ''romance,'' according to the dictionary, means excitement, adventure, and something extremely real. Romance should last a lifetime.', 4008, 0), (489911, 'If a June night could talk, it would probably boast it invented romance.', 59555, 0), (489912, 'I''m a feminist, but I think that romance has been taken away a bit for my generation. I think what people connect with in novels is this idea of an overpowering, encompassing love - and it being more important and special than anything and everything else.', 15748, 0), (489913, 'I''m a hopeless romantic. I buy things because I fall in love with them. I never buy anything just because it''s valuable.', 67408, 0), (489914, 'We believe that according the name ''investors'' to institutions that trade actively is like calling someone who repeatedly engages in one-night stands a ''romantic.''', 6410, 0), (489915, 'We only part to meet again.', 31023, 0), (489916, 'So the lover must struggle for words.', 1067, 0), (489917, 'It''s easy to get wrapped up in sharing everyday life with a partner. It''s fun to get lost in love and romance. It''s the best. But holding on to yourself while doing that is the most important thing.', 68009, 0), (489918, 'I am a romantic, and I think dates are wonderful. I like quirky and fun things. Like going for a bike ride or for a pedicure together.', 68008, 0), (489919, 'If I can give you one strong piece of advice, when you go away for that romantic weekend, whatever you do, do not accept or take the upgrade to the honeymoon suite.', 49687, 0), (489920, 'The male is always the pawn in a romantic comedy. Come together, break up, go chase her, get her, roll credits. That''s what happens in all of them.', 2387, 0), (489921, 'I love the concept of the romance that exists when people are broken. Like, the promise of a romance when you''re at the bottom. I think that''s infinitely compelling and romantic.', 69469, 0), (489922, 'I am a hopeless romantic and I love to spoil my girlfriends.', 68239, 0), (489923, 'The state of New Jersey is really two places - terrible cities and wonderful suburbs. I live in the suburbs, the final battleground of the American dream, where people get married and have kids and try to scratch out a happy life for themselves. It''s very romantic in that way, but a bit naive. I like to play with that in my work.', 439, 0), (489924, 'I''d always thought hurricanes were romantic, with pretty feminine names like Celestine.', 75750, 0), (489925, 'Am I a romantic? I''ve seen ''Wuthering Heights'' ten times. I''m a romantic.', 148, 0), (489926, 'I''m a hopeless romantic. It''s disgusting. It really is. I''ve seen ''While You Were Sleeping'', like, twenty times, and I still believe in the whole Prince Charming thing.', 2549, 0), (489927, 'You do your work as a photographer and everything becomes past. Words are more like thoughts; the photographer''s picture is always surrounded by a kind of romantic glamor - no matter what you do, and how you twist it.', 58218, 0), (489928, 'I am not an adolescent, nor a romantic. I analyze objectively.', 67398, 0), (489929, 'It''s glorious to be able to go onto the Internet and hear any kind of music anywhere, from anywhere, and get it instantly. But there''s also something glorious about having a record with a sleeve and looking at the artwork, putting it on the turntable and playing it, there''s still something romantic to me about that.', 69022, 0), (489930, 'I like sundresses with cowboy boots, little shorts with big wedge heels and a big piece of turquoise. I also love classic, Old Hollywood romantic styles. I''m ''country girl meets city girl'' circa 1930.', 74474, 0), (489931, 'In a big Bollywood romantic film, taking my shirt off and spreading the hand towards the mountain with dancers behind me are not my cup of tea.', 71314, 0), (489932, 'It gives me immense pleasure to be trustworthy, faithful, and true - to have the kind of romantic bond that inspires this.', 15511, 0), (489933, 'We are all the heroes and heroines of our own lives. Our love stories are amazingly romantic our losses and betrayals and disappointments are gigantic in our own minds. ', 556, 0), (489934, 'Romantic comedies are particularly hard to make.', 69723, 0), (489935, 'I don''t make romantic films. I make films about human relationships.', 72742, 0), (489936, 'I love being manipulated by what I see. I love weepies and romantic comedies where you''re reaching for the Kleenex at the right moment.', 2317, 0), (489937, 'Mixed messages are just part and parcel of the romantic terrain, and rather than berate yourself for any crossed wires, you''d do better to work on your future resilience.', 67020, 0), (489938, 'Great companies start because the founders want to change the world... not make a fast buck. Call me a romantic, but I think entrepreneurs should try to change the world. This comes from working at Apple... old habits die hard.', 5456, 0), (489939, 'Those fields of daisies we landed on, and dusty fields and desert stretches. Memories of many skies and earths beneath us - many days, many nights of stars.', 1407, 0), (489940, 'The more we are filled with thoughts of lust the less we find true romantic love.', 67402, 0), (489941, 'Everyone who knows me knows that I''m a hopeless romantic who listens to love ballads and doo-wop songs all the time.', 68, 0), (489942, 'In short I will part with anything for you but you.', 2618, 0), (489943, 'I have always been a romantic, one of those people who believes that a woman in pink circus tights contains all the secrets of the universe.', 105, 0), (489944, 'I''m a hopeless romantic and passionate person when it comes to love.', 24514, 0), (489945, 'I used to try to draw my girlfriends. I think one of the most romantic things that anybody can do is draw a portrait of the person you love.', 22992, 0), (489946, 'I am a better person when I let myself have the time for romance and for love.', 70263, 0), (489947, 'I used to be a hopeless romantic - I fell in love with everyone I went out with.', 69392, 0), (489948, 'I think romance is anything honest. As long as it''s honest, it''s so disarming.', 55840, 0), (489949, 'We must not, however, be like the leaders of the great romantic revolt who, in their eagerness to get rid of the husk of convention, disregarded also the humane aspiration.', 71965, 0), (489950, 'Consider what a romantic expedition you are on take notes. ', 75751, 0);
INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (489951, 'The compensation of a very early success is a conviction that life is a romantic matter. In the best sense one stays young.', 97, 0), (489952, 'Any romantic feelings for a 12-year-old are like entering into a fantasy world.', 74494, 0), (489953, 'I try to speak of a love that not necessarily romantic. I think there is so much love between people and so much love people want to give but it''s harder and harder these days to show that, to celebrate that, you know?', 67517, 0), (489954, 'I think romantic comedy, when done right, is my favorite genre. It''s just a genre that''s very human.', 2250, 0), (489955, 'If I eat a huge meal and I can get the girl to rub my belly, I think that''s about as romantic as I can think of.', 62003, 0), (489956, 'Building a little bonfire at night on the beach and lying on a blanket with my wife under the stars is not only sexy, it''s romantic.', 75752, 0), (489957, 'I guess I''m a bit of a romantic.', 69501, 0), (489958, 'I get some of my ideas from watching my three daughters, but most of them come from my own memories of growing up. I can remember how romantic I was, not just about love, but romance in the classic sense - the romantic ideals: of honor and truth, of loyalty, sacrifice and fairness. Those were the elements that made a story satisfying to me.', 12982, 0), (489959, 'If it''s a romantic holiday, the only thing I need is my wife. We love quiet and calm places where we can''t be disturbed. Neither of us likes being in busy places; we would much rather stay in our hotel room and enjoy each other''s company.', 71096, 0), (489960, 'I''ve seen plays that are, objectively, total messes that move me in ways that their tidier brethren do not. That''s the romantic mystery of great theater. Translating this ineffability into printable prose is a challenge that can never be fully met.', 75753, 0), (489961, 'I have a romantic conception of the writer''s life, and the sort of writer''s life that I admire is probably a childless life, possibly a marriageless life, certainly a travelling life - I''m in awe of how much D.H. Lawrence managed to get around. But that''s never been something I''m capable of doing.', 7476, 0), (489962, 'I was pleasantly disappointed on entering Bohemia. Instead of a dull, uninteresting country, as I expected, it is a land full of the most lovely scenery. There is every thing which can gratify the eye - high blue mountains, valleys of the sweetest pastoral look and romantic old ruins.', 57546, 0), (489963, 'I don''t want to be typecast as a heroine who does a certain kind of cinema, which is why I experiment with the types of films that I do. But yes, I won''t deny that romantic love stories or romantic comedies are what I enjoy doing the most, because as an audience those are the kind of films that I like watching.', 69743, 0), (489964, 'I am quite a romantic person, really, and I should have put that into my music earlier, but I was probably denying it... I didn''t want to be soft because I felt I had to be so hard to get people to believe in me.', 66903, 0), (489965, 'A shiny ring isn''t romantic to me. I think thought and love into what you do for the person you''re in love with - that''s romance.', 26862, 0), (489966, 'Surrealism was necessary - essential, even - in the 1920s to bridge the gap between rationalism and the subconscious. It started something important. But by the early ''60s, it had become petit-bourgeois; it was too intellectual and romantic, and had ground to a halt. It had become respectable.', 10194, 0), (489967, 'Vampires have become tragic or romantic figures. Vampire are largely seduction tales. They''re no longer the scary creature in the dark.', 23799, 0), (489968, 'I think the first time I tried to write a romantic song, it was just horrendously embarrassing. I remember thinking, ''Okay, I''m not going to do that anymore.'' I think that sort of embarrassed me for the next 10 years.', 71128, 0), (489969, 'My favorite genre is definitely romantic comedy. I love ''When Harry Met Sally.''', 69038, 0), (489970, 'If you are pro love, you have to be a little bit disloyal to the romantic feelings that propel you in the early days.', 639, 0), (489971, 'I''m personally a hopeless romantic. I always have been.', 72874, 0), (489972, 'When you hear romantic music, it makes you want to take your girl out to dinner or buy her something or take her out in the moonlight or take her on a walk.', 2025, 0), (489973, 'I personally think Prague is more romantic than Paris. If you have a girlfriend, take her there.', 67676, 0), (489974, 'I know most people use their phones to tell time, but there''s something very romantic and beautiful about a timepiece.', 24454, 0), (489975, 'I''m very romantic and of course I want to be in love.', 15748, 0), (489976, 'I admit I do have some drawbacks and limitations as a candidate. Although I am a professional comedian, some of my critics maintain that this is not enough. I cannot deny that I stand before you untested and inexperienced - I only spent two years in television, never as a romantic lead or a song and dance man.', 65734, 0), (489977, 'I find ''Fatal Attraction'' really romantic. I really like the seduction. Almost every time I see it, I''m surprised when it goes dark. I know that''s the claim to fame, but I key into how genuinely romantic it is.', 69469, 0), (489978, 'Sadly, people think a guy and a girl can''t be friends without something romantic going on.', 67358, 0), (489979, 'When I was 18, I thought that, to be a romantic, you couldn''t live past 30.', 1232, 0), (489980, 'I find television, and particularly live television, very romantic: the idea that there is this small group of people, way up high, in a skyscraper in the middle of Manhattan, beaming this signal out into the night.', 1482, 0), (489981, 'I''d like to be played as a child by Natalie Wood. I''d have some romantic scenes as Audrey Hepburn and have gritty black-and-white scenes as Patricia Neal.', 1739, 0), (489982, 'Usually comedy is only available to us ladies in the romantic comedy. That''s why I hate romantic comedies.', 68422, 0), (489983, 'When you''re in the throes of this romantic love, it''s overwhelming - you''re out of control, you''re irrational, you''re going to the gym at 6 A.M. every day - Why? Because she''s there.', 52746, 0), (489984, 'To write a novel is to embark on a quest that is very romantic. People have visions, and the next step is to execute them. That''s a very romantic project. Like Edvard Munch''s strange dreamlike canvases where people are stylized, like ''The Scream.'' Munch must have had that vision in a dream, he never saw it.', 852, 0), (489985, 'I absolutely love Ireland. It''s one of the most beautiful places on Earth, and I have strong ties here. Both my grandmothers are from Ireland, and I have spent every summer in Bantry since my father, who is an artist, had the romantic idea 20 years ago to buy an old farmhouse on the west coast and renovate it.', 67018, 0), (489986, 'Personally, I find it romantic not to be with someone all the time; you don''t get used to someone or take them for granted.', 47394, 0), (489987, 'Animals are everywhere. Some are more romantic, like tigers and elephants and chimpanzees, and some are less romantic, like earthworms, but they are just as interesting.', 70259, 0), (489988, 'Choosing sepia is all to do with trying to make the image look romantic and idealistic. It''s sort of a soft version of propaganda.', 70574, 0), (489989, 'You think, ''Musicals, they must always be romantic'' - You''d be surprised how few of them historically have ever been romantic.', 67678, 0), (489990, 'Bob Dole is not a romantic, at least not an immediate one. Bob Dole is not one to waste a lot of time on metaphor.', 27729, 0), (489991, 'In the early days of Christianity the exercise of chastity was frequently combined with a close and romantic intimacy of affection between the sexes which shocked austere moralists.', 62533, 0), (489992, 'I think I''ve only done one horror movie, Psycho III. That was a walk in the park compared to a romantic comedy.', 68048, 0), (489993, 'I don''t feel like a romantic lead I guess I feel more like a character actor. ', 74450, 0), (489994, 'Some have called we rock and roll performers who never retire ''troubadours.'' I enjoy this misnomer immensely. While there are many differences between me and my distant predecessors in L''Occitane, I do believe there is a lineage that connects us of the last 70 years with those romantic singers of the High Middle Ages.', 56251, 0), (489995, 'I was also the romantic lead in The Boston Strangler - I was the only one that lived to tell the story - so I called myself the romantic lead.', 75754, 0), (489996, 'Romantic art deals with the exception and with the individual. Good people, belonging as they do to the normal, and so, commonplace type, are artistically uninteresting.', 40, 0), (489997, 'They are just really stupid people in Hollywood. You write them a script, and they say they love it, they absolutely love it. Then they say, ''But doesn''t it need a small dog, and an Eskimo, and shouldn''t it be set in New Guinea?'' And you say, ''But it is a sophisticated romantic comedy set in Paris.''', 10731, 0), (489998, 'Kabul is a walled city, which sounds romantic except the walls are pre-cast reinforced concrete blast barriers, 10 feet tall and 15 feet long and moved into place with cranes. The walls are topped with sandbags, and the sandbags are topped with guard posts from which gun barrels protrude.', 10731, 0), (489999, 'It is possible for a woman to be a romantic, but also to be single and to be happy.', 100, 0), (490000, 'I love Indian, Italian and Mexican food. And if it''s a romantic type of thing, I like a good French restaurant.', 1300, 0);
